description:
‚Å£Caprese Chicken with Pesto üåøüçÖ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This dish is a perfect light dinner for the warm weather we‚Äôve been having and so easy to cook with hardly any ingredients needed! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Ingredients:‚†Ä
üçÖ1 chicken breast‚†Ä
üçÖ1 ball mozarella cheese ‚†Ä
üçÖ2 tomatoes ‚†Ä
üçÖsmall handful of basil ‚†Ä
üçÖpesto ‚†Ä
üçÖbalsamic glaze ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the chicken: ‚†Ä
preheat the oven to 180 degrees ‚†Ä
Chop your tomatoes ans mozarella into even slices ‚†Ä
Cut slices into the chicken breast deep enough for the stuffing ‚†Ä
Place the chicken breast on the oven tray and place slices of mozarella and tomato into the slices made in the chicken ‚†Ä
Top with 2 teaspoons of pesto, salt & pepper‚†Ä
Cook in the oven for roughly 30 mins till the chicken is cooked through ‚†Ä
Top with fresh basil & serve ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
For the caprese salad:‚†Ä
Lay out even slices of tomato and mozarella on your plate ‚†Ä
Lightly drizzle olive oil & balsamic glaze‚†Ä
Top with salt, pepper & fresh basil ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
Enjoy! ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This was delicious and minimum effort so is perfect for a weekday meal üòã‚†Ä

description:
Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

‚ú®Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce‚ú®

Ingredients:
‚úÖ2 lb bok choy, small 
‚úÖ1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
‚úÖ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
‚úÖ1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ‚úÖ6 Tbs tamari sauce 
‚úÖ1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds. 

üîÜFor more healthy recipes, click the link in bioü•∞

description:
Sweet & Savoury Mushroom Scones~üçÑ This easy and quick snack made with our favourite mushrooms is definitely a pleaser. We love having them with cream cheese, random toppings and even on its own.üòã Mama also made them petite so it's easy to pack them along as mini treats for the kids' outings! ‚ù§
.
Ingredients:
200g swiss brown mushrooms, chopped 
220g all purpose flour
20g sugar
6g baking powder
¬Ω tsp salt
1 tsp #lilomushroompowder
55g cold butter, cut into small cubes
25g beaten egg
Approx. 100ml milk 
.
Method:
‚úîIn a pan, saut√© chopped mushrooms with some butter till slightly brown and set aside to cool
‚úîCombine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and #lilomushroompowder in a bowl
‚úîRub in butter cubes with fingers until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs before adding in the saut√©ed mushrooms 
‚úîAdd in beaten egg and milk, and mix with a spatula until just combined with no dry flour remaining (add more milk if required)
‚úîTurn the dough out onto a floured surface and sprinkle some flour on top
‚úîPat the dough down lightly to about 3cm thick and cut straight down with a round cutter without twisting it
‚úîGather the loose pieces of dough into a ball and pat down again to cut out more
‚úîBrush the top of the scones with egg and bake in a preheated oven for 15-20 minutes at 180¬∞C till golden brown
.
.
.

combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and in a bowl

description:
Boscaiola! @rumourhasit9 had cooked this for my family and I and It‚Äôs now my go too for family meals. It‚Äôs a clean pasta that‚Äôs not too heavy, not too light and full of goodies.

Ingredients:
8 oz any mushrooms you can find
5-7 slices of prosciutto
1/3 cup sun dried tomato
1/4 cup white wine
2-3 sprigs of thyme
1 cup heavy cream
3 cloves garlic
2 Tbsp parsley
1 Tbsp butter
1/2 cup parmesan
12 oz pasta of choice
Optional: Chili flakes to your liking

-Finely chop your garlic, parsley, sun dried tomato, and thyme. -Thinly slice mushrooms and prosciutto.
-In a sauce pan on medium heat, add some oil and cook mushrooms till brown (5-7 mins). 
-Season with salt and pepper, then add a Tbsp of butter.
-Add the prosciutto. Once heated through add the garlic and chili flakes.
-Toss in the sun dried tomatoes and thyme, then deglaze with white wine.
-Once the white wine has reduced significantly, add the heavy cream and mix. 
-Let the flavors get to know each other then add your cooked pasta, parmesan and parsley.
-Give it a good mix, add some pasta water to thin out the sauce if needed.
-Serve and enjoy! üçù

description:
Hi besties! I thought it was time I‚Äôd share one of my all time favorite recipes. It‚Äôs a deliciously creamy coconut curry that I‚Äôve been making for a couple of years now. It‚Äôs the perfect comfort food in my opinion. 

THAI RED COCONUT CURRY CHICKEN
(ft my sous chef @izza.rehman & photographer @sa_herrr)
Ingredients:
* 1 pound thinly sliced chicken thighs 
* 1 jar Maesri red curry paste
* 2 tbsp lemongrass paste plus a teaspoon of fresh minced lemongrass 
* 1-2 diced shallots 
* 2 minced garlic cloves
* About an inch of minced ginger
*2 thinly sliced bell peppers 
* 1 can coconut milk
* 1 can coconut cream 
* 1 tbsp fish sauce (optional)
* a few Kaffir lime leaves 
* 2 tbsp brown sugar 
* 2 minced Thai chilies 
* 1/2 - 1 juiced lime
* 1/4 cup chopped Thai basil
*1/4 cup toasted cashews

-In a large pan, brown your chicken over medium high heat until no longer pink.
-Add your red curry paste along with the fresh lemongrass and lemongrass paste, garlic, ginger and shallot. Mix with the chicken and saut√© until aromatic. 
-Add your bell peppers and cook for a couple of more minutes and then bring the heat down to medium and add your coconut milk and cream. Let it simmer for a couple of minutes and then add the kaffir lime leaves, Thai chilies and brown sugar. 
-Stir well and cook for a few more minutes and then take off heat. 
-Add your Thai basil, toasted cashews and lime juice and serve over rice. Enjoy!

description:
These Creamy, Lemony Cucumber Sandwiches are perfect for lunches, get togethers and parties! üçãü•í They‚Äôre super easy to make in advance and taste incredible! ‚ú®

Save this post! Full recipe below! üëá

Ingredients: 

4 oz whole cream cheese, softened to room temp
2 TB chopped fresh dill
Zest and Juice of half a large lemon
Salted butter, softened for spreading on bread slices
kosher salt
freshly ground black pepper
6 slices high quality white or whole grain bread
1/2 large cucumber, seeded and thinly sliced, thoroughly dried with paper towels

Instructions: 

Combine: in a small bowl, combine cream cheese, fresh dill, lemon zest, and lemon juice. Add enough kosher salt and pepper to taste.

Assemble: butter each slice of bread (prevents sogginess.) Lay slices with butter-side-up on a work surface. Evenly distribute the cream cheese mixture onto each slice. Arrange towel-dried cucumber slices on top of the first 3 slices of bread. Top with remaining bread. Slice off the crusts. If not serving immediately, wrap tightly in cling wrap and chill for up to 24 hours.
Slice: when ready to serve, slice into 4 triangles per sandwich. Cover and chill any leftovers.

description:
No-Bake Salted Chocolate Tahini Tart üç´ü•ß‚Å†
.‚Å†
A rich, crunchy chocolate crust and silky ganache filling AND no bake time? This one is almost too good to be true.‚Å†
.‚Å†
Chocolate // Graham crackers // Tahini // Fresh fruit‚Å†
.‚Å†
Ingredients:‚Å†
‚Å†
Crust‚Å†
600g chocolate graham cracker crumb‚Å†
1/2 cup butter, melted‚Å†
¬Ω tsp salt, to taste‚Å†
‚Å†
Filling‚Å†
10 oz chocolate, melted (dark or semi-sweet)‚Å†
1.5 cups full fat, 35% cream‚Å†
1/3 cup tahini‚Å†
‚Å†
Garnish‚Å†
Fresh fruit‚Å†
¬Ω tsp maldon or flaky salt‚Å†
.‚Å†
Directions:‚Å†
‚Å†
For the Crust‚Å†
1. Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs until a thick sandy mixture develops.‚Å†
2. Season with salt and press into a tart pan lined with parchment. Chill in the fridge.‚Å†
‚Å†
For the Filling‚Å†
1. In a pot, scald the cream. Remove from heat and add in the chocolate and tahini.‚Å†
2. Once combined, pour the mixture into the chilled tart mold.‚Å†
3. Place in the fridge for 45 minutes to set fully. ‚Å†
‚Å†
For the Garnish‚Å†
1. Garnish with fruit of your choice and finish with maldon or flaky salt.‚Å†
.‚Å†
.‚Å†
.‚Å†

description:
Warm salad of purple sprouting broccoli, new potatoes and #ParmigianoReggiano üòç

INGREDIENTS:
- 400g New potatoes, preferably Charlotte
- 20g Hazelnuts, blanched
- 200g Purple sprouting broccoli, trimmed of its thick stalks
- ¬Ω Red onion, thinly sliced (approx. 75g)
- 20g Parmigiano Reggiano
- 20g Flat leaf parsley, leaves picked from the stalks (big handful)
- 6 Basil leaves (2.5g)
- 1 Tarragon sprig, leaves picked (1g)
- 1 small clove garlic
- 2 anchovy fillets, from a tin (optional)
- ¬Ω tsp Dijon mustard
- ¬Ω Lemon, juiced, the rest kept for garnish

METHOD:
1. Boil the potatoes until cooked, approx. 15 minutes, then drain.
2. Make a garlic paste by smashing it with salt with the back of your knife. Add to the picked herbs and the anchovies and chop finely. Put in a bowl and mix with the mustard, lemon juice, olive oil and black pepper.
3. Toast the hazelnuts in a dry pan for a few minutes. Use a pestle and mortar or similar to coarsely crush the hazelnuts.
4. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in the same frying pan. Add the broccoli and sliced onion and a splash of water. Cover and saut√©/steam until broccoli cooked al dente. Remove lid and boil off any water left in pan. Season and empty into large bowl.
5. Thickly slice the potatoes and add to the pan, with a splash more olive oil if needed. Fry for a couple of minutes to reheat. Season well.
6. Add the dressing to the bowl and coat everything.

description:
.A Complete 5 week meal plan with Quick start guide, Shopping list and Recipes ( Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, Salad, Sides, Essentials ) Link in Bio üîó @keto_daily_meals
.
.
.
.

Ingredients:

1/2 lb. farfalle
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped
1 tsp olive oil
3 large garlic cloves, minced
4 plant based sausages (396 g)
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tsp dried parsley
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1 cup (packed) baby spinach
1 cup canned crushed tomatoes
1 cup dairy free heavy cream

Instructions:

Cook farfalle in salted water according to package directions, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water prior to draining.

Meanwhile, preheat large pan on medium heat. Add onions and oil, cook on medium low for 10 min, adding 1/2 cup water to prevent burning if needed and stirring periodically. Add minced garlic and crumble in the sausages. Stir, add all the seasonings, and cook for 6 to 8 min, stirring periodically, until starting to brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 to 3 min, stirring as spinach wilts. Add pasta, stir, add pasta cooking water if desired. Serve with red chili flakes and basil if desired.
.
.
.

description:
If you are looking to bring a yummy pasta salad to the next outdoor summer BBQ, try out this amazing Grilled Ratatouille Pasta Salad!

Ingredients: 

‚àô 2 medium zucchini (about 1¬Ω lb.), halved lengthwise
‚àô About 1 lb Adagio¬Æ Eggplants , cut into 1" wedges
‚àô ¬æ cup extra-virgin olive oil, divided
‚àô 2¬Ω tsp. kosher salt, divided
‚àô 1 tsp. freshly ground black pepper, divided
‚àô 10 oz. penne or casarecce pasta
‚àô 1 large or 2 medium Heirloom or Virtuoso¬Æ Beefsteak Tomatoes (about 1 lb.), cut into 1" pieces
‚àô 8 oz. Ciliegini (mini fresh mozzarella balls), drained, halved
‚àô 2 Tbsp. white balsamic or white wine vinegar
‚àô 1 Tbsp. thyme leaves
‚àô 1 cup basil leaves

Instructions:

1. Prepare a grill for medium heat. Toss zucchini, eggplant, and ¬º cup oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with 1 tsp. salt and ¬Ω tsp. pepper. Grill, turning often, until steamy, tender, and charred all over, 8‚Äì12 minutes. Return to the baking sheet and let cool.

2. Cook pasta according to package directions.

3. Slice grilled vegetables into bite-size pieces and transfer to a large bowl. Add tomato, cheese, vinegar, thyme, and 1¬Ω tsp. salt, ¬Ω tsp. pepper, and ¬Ω cup oil and mix to combine. Drain pasta and immediately add to the bowl with vegetables. Mix well to combine, then top with basil.

description:
Need an easy brunch recipe? This Plant-Basedüå± Breakfast Casserole is so simple and so tasty! It‚Äôs a great vegan recipe for brunch and it feeds at least 8 people. And the key to this dish, is the savory kick from the plant-based @eatlocafood LOCA Foods potato queso! It is just such a delicious recipe! So whether or not your guests are vegetarian, vegan, or meat-eaters, they‚Äôll enjoy this dish! 

Get these ingredients, and try this recipe for your breakfast tomorrow, it won't disappoint!

INGREDIENTS:

description:
This Chocolate Pancake  is a must try for all chocolate lovers. 

Use Trust range of sugars for the perfect balance of sweetness and taste.

Repost @homecookingshow

Ingredients:
-Maida - 1 1/3 Cup
-Cocoa Powder - 4 Tbsp
-Baking Powder - 2 Tsp
-Sugar - 3 Tbsp
-Chocolate Chip - 2 Tbsp
-Salt - 1/4 Tsp
-Egg - 1 No.
-Milk - 1 Cup
-Melted Butter - 1/4 Cup
-Vanilla Essence - 1/4 Tsp
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Butter

Chocolate ganache
-Fresh Cream - 1/2 Cup
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Semi-sweet Cooking Chocolate - 100 Gms

Method:
-To make pancakes
-In a medium bowl whisk together egg until creamy. Add in milk and melted butter, and whisk until combined well.
-In another bowl whisk dry ingredients and add them into the wet ingredients. Whisk until combined well. It will be a thick batter. Fold in chocolate chips.
- Heat a pan over medium heat and either spread a little butter over it.
- Scoop the batter onto the pan using a 1/4 cup for each pancake.
- Cook until you see bubbles on the top, for about 1 minute or so.
-Flip them over and cook for another 1 minute.
-Transfer to a serving plate and repeat with the remaining batter.
-Serve pancakes with chocolate ganache

To make the Chocolate Ganache
-Heat heavy cream and milk in a saucepan.
-Add chocolate chunks and stir well until it turns into a smooth and silky ganache.
-Wait until it reaches room temperature before pouring it over pancakes

description:
overnight oats üçØ if you‚Äôre wanting some easy and deLISH breakfast inspiration, you need these overnight oats at the top of your list! I‚Äôve been making it in 3-day batches and I can‚Äôt get enough ü§§ recipe below - brands tagged for reference!

Overnight oats (makes 3 portions)

Ingredients:
- 1.5 cups @quakeroatsuk oats
- 2 scoops unflavoured or vanilla @bulk protein powder
- 1/2 tsp cinnamon
- 1.5-2 cups milk of choice (I use @alpro) 
- 2/3 cup greek yoghurt
- 2 tbsp chia seeds
- maple syrup to taste (I used about 1 tbsp)
- 1 tsp vanilla essence (omit if using vanilla protein)
- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips

method:
- mix together the oats, protein powder and cinnamon
- add the rest of the ingredients and mix together until we‚Äôll combined
- pour into an airtight container (or multiple if you want them in pre-prepped portions)
- store in the fridge for up to three days. Serve topped with fresh strawberries üçì and @pipandnut peanut butter

description:
Finally got round to making baba ganoush! Not sure why but I thought it was going to be way more effort than it was. TASTED UNBELIEVABLE ü§§ no blender needed. 

Ingredients: 
2 aubergines 
2 minced garlic cloves 
2 tablespoons lemon juice 
1/4 cup tahini 
1/3 cup olive oil 
2 tbsp chopped flat leaf parsley
1/4 tsp cumin 
Salt n peps 
Sprinkle of paprika 

Method:
~ preheat oven to 230 degrees c 
~ chop your aubergines in half lengthwise and brush cut sides with olive oil 
~ place them skin side up on baking paper lined tray and bake in oven for 35-40 mins 
~ when done, scoop out aubergine flesh and strain flesh to get rid of liquid 
~ put in bowl, add garlic and lemon juice, and whisk with a fork to break down the aubergine 
~ add tahini and stir till combined 
~ while stirring, slowly drizzle in olive oil 
~ once all broken down and mixed together, add in salt, cumin and parsley 
~ add more lemon juice to taste 
~ transfer to a pretty bowl and drizzle with more olive oil and a sprinkle of paprika and parsley 

Voila! I chopped up some pitta breads and roasted them in olive oil, salt n peps and rosemary to scoop up the deliciousness with. 

#babaganoush #aubergine #foodie #foodism #foodismedicine #foodislife #recipe #recipeoftheday #recipeideas

description:
CHOCOLATE BAKED OATS üòã I love chocolate and I love cake - they‚Äôre the two things that in the past would usually let me down when I tried to follow a healthy eating regime. Thanks to all the inspiration here I‚Äôm finding ways to still have my cake and eat it (lol!) while not undoing my hard work. I baked this last night to eat this morning and it was yummy! It works out as 4 syns and 320 calories per portion. Recipe below - I made this for me and my husband, so just half the ingredients if it‚Äôs just for one personüîª

Ingredients:
16 Aero chocolate melts - 8 melts per person at 1/2 syn per melt (4 syns per portion)
80g oats (40g = 1 HEXb)
60ml semi skimmed milk (1/4 HEXa)
1/3 cup zero calorie sweetener (free)
2 eggs (free)
2 tsp vanilla essence (free)
1 tsp baking powder 

1. Preheat your oven at gas mark 5/6 or 180 degrees Celsius. Grease a baking dish with cooking spray.
2. Blitz your oats in a food processor and then mix into a bowl with 1/3 cup sweetener and 1 tsp baking powder.
3. Crack 2 eggs into the bowl and mix thoroughly.
4. Add 2 tsp vanilla essence and 60ml of semi skimmed milk and stir the batter again.
5. Fold in 16 Aero melts - 8 melts per portion is 4 syns.
6. Pop into the oven for half an hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Leave to cool before eating!

description:
Spicy Tuna Pancake/Gochu-Chamchi Jeon!(·ÑÄ·Ö©·Ñé·ÖÆ·Ñé·Ö°·Ü∑·Ñé·Öµ·Ñå·Ö•·Ü´) 

Sharing another easy and tasty dish you can enjoy any day of the week! Recently, you guys may have seen my story photos, I had received a wonderful box of Korean products from @kseafoodusa. It included a nice variety of pantry items from Korea: like roasted seaweed, canned tuna, seaweed crackers, nori sheets and more! Thanks to them I was able to make this delicious jeon!! Recipe below!ü§óü§ó

Ingredients:
Gochu chamchi (spicy tuna) 1 can 
1/2 c diced onion
1/2 T garlic minced
2T scallion, chopped
3/4 buchim garoo (korean pancake mix)
pinch black pepper

1)Open can and drain tuna for 5-10min 
2)Combine all ingredients into a mixing bowl, without over mixing. 
3)Heat pan and cook jeon until golden brown on both sides, in med low heat. Drop about 2tbsp for each jeon. Makes about 9 pc. total. Enjoy with favorite dipping sauce!! üòãüòã

These were super tasty and not fishy at all!! I didn't need to add any salt or seasoning since the canned tuna was already seasoned and had a nice savory kick to it!ü§óü§ó 

And look for these brands if you want to try some high quality Korean seafood!!üëçüëç
.
.
.

description:
Macro Friendly Chicken Enchiladas ü•ë 

Ingredients:
Whipped FF cream cheese, 80 g
Salsa Verde, 60 g (1/4 cup)
1 Tbs lime juice
1 tsp chili powder
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/3 cup cilantro
Green onions, as much as desired
2 cups shredded chicken (Any kind you want! Great if you have leftovers from a different night. In this photo, I used an HEB rotisserie chicken!)
10 extra thin mission corn tortillas
1 can red enchilada sauce
3 oz lite Mexican cheese

Directions:
(1) Mix your cream cheese, salsa verde, lime juice, and all the seasonings together. Add in cilantro, green onions, & shredded/diced chicken. Combine.

(2) Warm your corn tortillas in the microwave for 10 to 15 seconds until flexible. Divide the chicken and cream cheese mixture evenly amongst the 10 tortillas. Place them seem side down in a greased baking dish.

(3) Cover the enchiladas with the sauce & shredded cheese. Bake it for 25 for about 10-15 min. 

Serve hot! The guacamole shown is not included in the macros but it‚Äôs highly encouraged as an add-on üòò.

Macros per Enchilada:
Cals: 168
Protein: 15.1
Carbs: 19.2
Fat: 3.4

description:
HEALTHY & EASY BANANA BREAD MUFFINSüçåüßÅ

I‚Äôve recently injured my knee again and currently I‚Äôm baking as a way to cope. These muffins took less then 30 minutes and I‚Äôm not ashamed to say these will be gone by tonight:.)

Ingredients:
2 ripe bananas, mashed 
1/3 cup olive oil 
1/2 cup maple syrup 
2 eggs 
1/2 tsp vanilla 

2 cups flour 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp baking soda 
1/2 tsp salt 

Preheat oven to 350
Add the wet ingredients to a bowl and mix. In a separate bowl add the dry ingredients and mix. Then, fold the dry mixture into the wet until everything is combined. Add muffin liners to a muffin pan or grease your muffin tins, and pour the batter to at least half way full (mine made 11). Bake for 25 minutes and enjoy:)

description:
I've been LOVING having overnight oats for breakfast lately. üòã They're so quick and easy to make and they last up to five days in the fridge (so you can meal prep breakfast for the week)! üòç Plus, there are endless things you can add to them so you never get tired of eating the same thing!

Here's a recipe for my go-to flavor at the moment...

Super easy blueberry overnight oats!

Ingredients:
- ‚Öî cup rolled oats
- ‚Öî cup milk, of your choice
- ¬Ω cup vanilla greek yogurt
- ¬Ω teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1 teaspoon chia seed, optional
- ¬Ω teaspoon cinnamon
- 2 teaspoons of something sweet like honey, berry jam, or maple syrup
- handful of fresh blueberries

Directions:
1. In a mason jar or sealable container, add the oats, milk, yogurt, vanilla extract, chia seeds, cinnamon and blueberries and stir together.
2. Seal and place in the refrigerator overnight for up to five days.
3. Top with your something sweet and blueberries.
4. Give it a good stir and enjoy! ü§ó

description:
‚Ä¢ Lunch (or dinner) idea ‚Ä¢

The most amazing toasted sarnie, yesterday I really didn‚Äôt fancy using the oven as it was so hot! So whipped up these Tomato & Mozzarella toasties instead and boy were they good üëåüèº

Ingredients:
Sourdough bread
Pesto
Large tomatoes 
Mozzarella 
Roasted red peppers

Method:
Spread pesto onto each slice of bread, add one slice of bread to your George Foreman grill, top with tomatoes, mozzarella & peppers then add second slice of bread & close grill. Leave for 2-3 mins until cheese has melted & tomatoes have softened.

Calories per serving approx: 492kcals

I‚Äôd love to hear if you give this lunch idea a try and don‚Äôt forget to tag me in your foodie pictures üòÉ

Emma

description:
RECIPE DROP: Pepperoni, Harissa & Yoghurt Pasta

using @properoni_uk Hot Paprika Pepperoni because it‚Äôs the BESTüî•

This dish is SO tasty and SO easy. Now, you will need a food processor or meat grinder but apart from that this could not be simpler üí™üèª

Ingredients: 
- 2 whole pepperoni sausages, casings removed and finely chopped in a food processor
- 1 bunch flat-leaf parsley chopped
- 75g harissa (we are big fans of rose harissa)
- Juice of 2 lemons
- 500g pasta (we used pappardelle)
- 280g thick Greek-style yoghurt

Steps:
1. Add ground pepperoni and parsley stalks to a frypan over medium-low heat and cook, stirring until crispy
2. Stir in the harissa and 250ml water. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes until thickened
3. Stir through the lemon juice and chopped parsley
4. Remove from the heat and season with salt and pepper
5. Cook the pasta
6. Now to serve. Spread yoghurt over plates/shallow bowls
7. Add pasta on top, and spoon over meat sauce
8. Finish with reserved parsley and lemon juice
.
.
.
.
.

description_preprocessed:
recipe drop: pepperoni, harissa & yoghurt pasta

using hot paprika pepperoni because it‚Äôs the best

this dish is so tasty and so easy. now, you will need a food processor or meat grinder but apart from that this could not be simpler 

ingredients: 
- 2 whole pepperoni sausages, casings removed and finely chopped in a food processor
- 1 bunch flat-leaf parsley chopped
- 75 gram harissa (we are big fans of rose harissa)
- juice of 2 lemons
- 500 gram pasta (we used pappardelle)
- 280 gram thick greek-style yoghurt

steps:
1 . add ground pepperoni and parsley stalk to a frypan over medium-low heat and cook, stirring until crispy
2 . stir in the harissa and 250 ml water. bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes until thickened
3 . stir through the lemon juice and chopped parsley
4 . remove from the heat and season with salt and pepper
5 . cook the pasta
6 . now to serve. spread yoghurt over plates/shallow bowls
7 . add pasta on top, and spoon over meat sauce
8 . finish with reserved parsley and lemon juice
.
.
.
.
.

description:
Oreo tiffin/traybake üç´

This Oreo flavoured no bake traybake is super easy and quick to make and perfect for summer picnics or BBQs. It‚Äôs also ideal to make when it‚Äôs warm as it doesn‚Äôt require an oven. 

Ingredients:
‚ñ™Ô∏è100g butter- @bakewithstork 
‚ñ™Ô∏è1 tbsp sugar free syrup*- @nkdliving 
‚ñ™Ô∏è80g golden blond choc spread- @marksandspencerfoodpr 
‚ñ™Ô∏è230g Oreos- @oreouki 
‚ñ™Ô∏è80g raisins and cranberries- @hollandandbarrett 
‚ñ™Ô∏è150g white chocolate- @droetkerbakes 
‚ñ™Ô∏è120g cookies and cream spread- @marksandspencerfoodpr 

* if you don‚Äôt have sugar free syrup, use golden syrup or similar sugar free syrup.

Method:
1. Line a 20x20cm baking tin with parchment. Melt the butter, syrup, white chocolate and blond chocolate spread on the hob/stove until melted.
2. Crush the Oreos into chunks and add most of these (leave some behind for the top) and the dried fruit and mix well. Pour into your lined tin and flatten.
3. Melt your cookies and cream spread until smooth. Pour over your tiffin base, sprinkle the remaining Oreo chunks on top and place in the fridge to set for 3 hours. Once set, remove and leave at room temperature for 1 hour before pouring hot water over your knife to make it easier to cut. Enjoy!

Please let me know if you recreate/get inspo! ‚ú®

description:
Inflammation means when your body tries to defend itself from things that might harm it, in other words it's your body defense/healing mechanism. 

This process becomes harmful when it becomes chronic, leaving your body in a constant 'alert' mode. Over time, chronic inflammation can damage your healthy cells, tissues and organs. 

Often subtle, symptoms of chronic inflammation can be fatigue, bodily pain, anxiety/depression, gastrointenstinal issues, weight gain/loss and infections

Smoking, obesity, chronic stress and alcohol can contribute to chronic inflammation. Lifestyle changes such as stress management, a healthy diet, plenty of water and exercise can help enormously. 

Help calm your body and fight inflammation by blending up this vibrant anti-inflammatory smoothie that is loaded with vitamins, minerals, fiber, and deliciousness! 

Ingredients:
4 oranges (peeled & cut) 
2 carrots (peeled & cut) 
Ginger (half thumb or 1/4 tsp ginger powder) 
Turmeric (half thumb or 1/4 tsp turmeric powder) 
Pinch of pepper 
2 tbsp fres aloe (gel, optional)
Water (1/4 - 1/2 cup) 

Instructions:
Blend all ingredients in a high speed blender.
Add more water if too thick. Serve cold and enjoy! 

Will you be trying this smoothie? Comment  below ‚¨áÔ∏è

description:
Irresistible almond-oat cookies ‚Äì Can‚Äôt get enough of these easy-to-make bites loaded with all the good stuff! Make an extra batch. They keep extramely well in a covered container.
 
Œó œÉœÖŒΩœÑŒ±Œ≥ŒÆ œÉœÑŒ± ŒµŒªŒªŒ∑ŒΩŒπŒ∫Œ¨, œÉœÑŒ± œÉœáœåŒªŒπŒ± Œ∫Œ±Œπ œÉœÑŒø œÄœÅŒøœÜŒØŒª ŒºŒøœÖ œÉœÑŒø œÜŒ±œÑœÉŒøŒ≤ŒπŒ≤ŒªŒØŒø.
 
INGREDIENTS:
170 g ‚ÄúLeivadiotis‚Äù raw almonds
120 g whole oats
120 g all-purpose flour
¬Ω tsp baking powder
¬º tsp salt
125 g unsalted butter
120 g soft brown sugar
1 large egg
1 tsp vanilla extract
About 24 whole almonds to garnish
.

METHOD:
Roast almonds at 175 C fan, for 10 minutes. Cool and chop roughly in a small chopper. Set aside until needed.
In a bowl, mix together the oats, flour, baking powder and salt.
In a mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Mix in egg and vanilla extract. Add oat-flour mixture and mix on low speed until combined. Finally add the almonds and mix again.
With a cookie scoop or spoon, make walnut sized balls and place on oven trays, lined with greaseproof paper or silicon mats. Press each cookie slightly with your hands to flatten slightly. Press a whole almond in the centre.
Cool unbaked cookies in the fridge for 1 hour. After this stage you can either bake them or place in zip-lock bags and store in the freezer.
Bake cookies at 175 C fan (pre-heated) for 13-15 minutes. If baking from the freezer, bake in a non-preheated oven. Cool on a wire rack. Cookies will be soft when hot but will harden as they cool.
 
#oatcookies #oats #almonds #healthyfood #vegetarian #biscuits @leivadiotisnuts
.

description:
üòâ Take a look at how @eatsimply02 put together her ultimate comfort dish - Cheesy Tomato Fusilli recipe with her favourite Ayam Brand Baked Beans Vegetarian amid the breathtaking scenery of ‚õ∞Ô∏è Cradle Mountain. 

üòã Give this recipe a try and you are in for a treat. Remember to tag your vegetarian friend too! 

Ingredients: 
- 425g Ayam Brand Baked Beans - Vegetarian 
- ¬º Zucchini (cut into small cubes)
- 4 big Cherry Tomato (sliced)
- 2 tbsp Parmesan Cheese
- Few dashes Black Pepper
- Few dashes Italian herbs

Preparation: 
1. Add baked beans, zucchini and cherry tomatoes to the cooking pot. Bring it to boil then simmer for 5 minutes. Stir occasionally. (Concurrently, cook fusilli according to instructions.)
2. Stir in parmesan cheese, black pepper and Italian herbs until cheese has melted into the sauce.
3. Pour the sauce onto the fusilli. Serve immediately.

description:
Banana and vanilla cheesecake with raspberry compote, raspberry curd and fresh strawberries üçì Sweetened using fruits and honey. This dessert has been inspired by our visit to the Holy Island of Lindisfarne 

We visited the Lindisfarne Priory @englishheritage and what a wonderful experience this was! In picture 4 I have attempted to write ‚Äúlove to cook‚Äù using Lindisfarne alphabet. Picture 5 is perhaps of interest only to @n.mcdonald2 

Standing in the middle of the Priory kitchen and bakehouse I felt like baking something fresh and fruity. Also got ourselves some delicious raspberry curd and this was so very tasty with our #homemadecheesecake . On our way to the car park we also bought some delicious local strawberries. 

@englishheritage , I hope it is OK for me to post some pictures of the Priory kitchen, bakehouse and brewhouse. I sought permission at the visitor centre and was told it would be fine. If not please let me know and I will remove these. 

For 6-8 portions. 
Ingredients:
1. Good quality cream. I used organic cream from @baysleaporganic. 3 tablespoons 
2. Lighter, high protein cream cheese. X 2 165 gm tubs
3. 2 eggs, I used organic eggs
4. 3 tablespoons self raising flour 
5. Honey, I used English blossom honey from @englishheritage 
6. 2 very ripe bananas 
7. Vanilla extract/ paste, a drop 
8. Zest of a lemon 
9. Jaggery, to sprinkle on top if you please 
10. Raspberry compote: raspberries, honey. Microwave for a couple of minutes, sweeten to your taste using honey. Chill overnight. 

Enjoy with some fruit curd, eg: raspberry curd. We got ours from @englishheritage visitors shop 

Method: 
1. Combine bananas, cream cheese, cream, eggs, flour and vanilla extract. Taste and sweeten using honey 
2. Empty into a baking tray lined with moistened baking paper
3. Sprinkle with jaggery and bake at 180C x 20 minutes till the top is golden and more importantly the cheesecake has a mild wobble in the centre. 
4. Turn oven off and keep cheesecake in for another 30-40 minutes 
5. Chill overnight 

#holyislandoflindisfarne #lindisfarne #cheesecake #fruity #healthierdessert #easydessert #fruitydessert #raspberries #fruits #honey #dessertlover #recipeoftheday

description:
This wild rice pilaf recipe creates a side dish that‚Äôs full of delicious flavor while being an easy and healthy! üçö‚ú®

Save this post! Full recipe below! üëá

Ingredients: 

2 cups wild rice blend (such as Lundgren‚Äôs)
Regular strength chicken or vegetable broth (enough to use instead of water, for cooking rice according to package instructions)
1/4 cup salted butter, sliced
1 large onion, chopped
1 cup thinly sliced baby carrots
2 cups freshly shaved brussels sprouts
4 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp dry Italian seasoning
1/4 tsp freshly ground black pepper

Instructions: 

Cook rice according to package instructions, using the broth instead of water. When cook time is up, do not open lid; turn heat off and keep lid tightly covered for 10 minutes to allow continued steaming. If rice is still a bit too firm, mix in just enough extra broth to moisten all rice, cover, and simmer another 10 minutes.
While rice is cooking, add butter to a large/deep skillet over medium high heat. Once butter is melted and starting to bubble, add onion and carrots. Stir to combine. Cover and cook 5 minutes,  stirring occasionally. Add brussels sprouts, garlic, Italian seasoning, and black pepper, stirring another 2 minutes until softened. 
Check rice for doneness. Fluff with fork and add to skillet with vegetable mixture, stirring to incorporate. Taste and season with kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper as needed.

description:
Come dig in (dip in?) to some of the greatest Superfood Hummus around. It is easy to make, and bursting with flavor, protein, and super green vitamins and minerals! üå±üí™

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 15-ounce can Chickpeas, drained and rinsed
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Tahini 
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Italian parsley
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Super greens of choice (a packed cup of raw greens) such as kale, arugula, and/or spinach.
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Chives or green onion, chopped
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Lemon juice, fresh-squeezed
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Olive oil
‚Ä¢ 1-2 cloves Fresh garlic (peeled) ‚Äì depending on your affinity for garlic
‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp Cumin
‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Sea salt 
‚Ä¢ Dash of black pepper
‚Ä¢ 1 scp of Creamy Vanilla Superfood Protein
‚Ä¢ Possibly a small splash of water during blending

Directions:
1. Combine all of the above-listed ingredients in a food processor or high-powered blender (such as a Vitamix) and pulse/blend until combined.
2. Don‚Äôt add any water to your green hummus until you blend everything else first. Then, if it seems still seems too thick, slowly add just a tablespoon or two of water at a time, blend, and re-assess.
3. Do a taste-test after mixing but before calling the green hummus ‚Äúdone‚Äù. Add more salt, pepper, or other seasonings if desired.
4. Serve your lusciously-green hummus in a bowl with your favorite dip-able items.
5. Store in an air-tight container in the refrigerator, and use within 5-7 days.

#PlantBasedRecipes #Hummus

description:
üçÖ|Rigatoni with Pork Ragu|üê∑ 

Best pasta sauce I've made and here's how I made it.
-TY

Ingredients:
-Spare ribs (2x packs)
-Sausages (1x pack)
-Chorizo (1x)
-Olive oil
-Onion (3x)
-Celery (3√ó)
-Carrot (3x)
-Tomatos (3x packs cherry/plum) 
-Passata
-Tomato paste
-Garlic (3x cloves)
-Red wine (200-250ml)
-Basil (1x pack)
-Bay leaf (6x)
-Salt and Pepper
-Rigatoni 
-Pasta water
-Parmesan 

1) Salt and pepper spare ribs.
2) Prep vegetables, dice them up! 
3) Saut√© spare ribs to add some colour, remove and add chorizo + sausages (remove sausage from casing).
4) Remove sausage and chorizo. Add diced veggies in. Sweat until soft (stir) then add tomato paste.
5) Add tomatos and passata. Sweat until soft. Blend til smooth.
6) Add all the meats back in with red wine + basil + Bay leaf.
7) Cover and slow cook for at least 2hrs in oven 160¬∞C 
8) Remove casserole pot from oven and remove Bay leaf and Spare ribs. Remove the meat of the rib bones (watch out it'll be HOT!)
9) Cook Rigatoni with salted water til "al dented". 
10) Spoon some of the ragu into a pan. Add pasta water (slowly add, avoid adding too much). 
11) Add Rigatoni to the Ragu.
12) Serve with parmesan.

.
.
.
#italianfood #italiancuisine #italian #pasta #sauce #rigatoni #ragu #porkragu #spareribs #sausage #homecooking #homecooked #homemade #recipeoftheday #recipeshare #basil #homechef #cookingforfun #cookingathome #hotfood #tastyfood #eatrealfood #eatwellbewell #yaucancookit #stayhealthy

description:
This a-MAIZE-zing and flavorful corn salad will surprise and SHUCK you! Blasting with bold flavors and textures, it‚Äôs definitely a must try in our book! üåΩüåøüßÄ üçãü§§

Ingredients: 
3 cans sweet corn rinsed and drained 
3 tablespoons salted butter 
3/4 teaspoon cumin 
3/4 teaspoon chili powder 
1/2 teaspoon pepper 
1/2 teaspoon salt 
1/2 large red onion, chopped 
1 jalape√±o, chopped 
3/4 cup cotija cheese, crumbled (more for garnish) 
2 tablespoons cilantro (more for garnish) 
Lime wedges to garnish 

Dressing 
1 cup mayonnaise, such as Hellmann‚Äôs 
1 cup heavy cream 
Juice of 2 times 
1/2 teaspoon chili powder 
Salt to taste 

Directions: 
1. Combine ingredients for dressing in a bowl. Taste to adjust seasonings and place in refrigerator until ready to use
2. In large skillet, melt butter and add corn. Cook until corn is slightly charred. May take 20- 30 minutes.
3. Allow corn to cool in a large bowl and then add remaining ingredients 
4. Toss with as much dressing as you like. (The rest can be used as a condiment for tacos or quesadillas.)
5. Garnish with more cotija, cilantro, and lime wedges. Enjoy!

description:
Recipe time!!

Boil your lasagna for 5-7 minutes and run cold water over it once its boiled! Keep it aside.

Chicken Minced Ingredients: 

- Half kg Chicken minced
- 1 Medium sized Onion finely chopped 
- 3-4 medium sized tomatoes (paste)
- Ginger garlic paste 2 TB spoon (Because I LOVEEE)
- Salt (as per taste)
- Paprika powder, 1 TB spoon (or as per your taste)
- Oregano (half tea spoon)
- Mixed Herms (as per your liking)
- Soya sauce 1 TB spoon
- Chilli sauce 1 TB spoon
- Chilli garlic ketchup (3-4 TB spoons ü•Ñ)

Method: Saut√© your onion in half tb spoon oil, add ginger garlic paste and cook it until your onion becomes transparent, add chicken minced and saut√© nicely for about 4-5 Mins, add tomato paste, all the spices and sauces and let it cook for almost 20 mins or until the water dries up.

White Sauce Ingredients:
- Butter (3-4 TB spoon)
- Maida- all purpose flour - (4-5 TB spoon)
- Milk around 1-1.5 Cups, depends on your consistency
- Black pepper (1 tea spoon)
- Salt (as per your liking)
- White pepper (1 tea spoon)
- Oregano (half tea spoon)
- Mixed herbs (half tea spoon)

Method: Add butter in your pan, once its melted, add flour and keep wisking, gradually add milk while mixing the mixture, add all your spices and herbs, make sure you‚Äôre continuously mixing so there‚Äôs no lumps in the sauce. Once you get your desired consistency, turn off the flame. 

Preparation: In a ovenproof dish, Make a layer of your lasagna sheets, top it with your minced mixture, drop some white sauce on it, garnish with mushrooms and olives, put some (A LOT) cheese, I used mozzarella and cheddar!

Keep repeating the layers! Make the last layer of lasagna sheet, mushrooms, olives, Oregano and cheese.
Bake it for 20-25 mins, once its done, Broil it for 5-7 mins or once the cheese is completely melted and the crust is nicely golden! ü§ç 

TADAAA! Done.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#recipes #lasagna #italianfood #italiandish #recipeoftheday #food #foodblogger #cook

description:
üåØ Spicy Mexican RiceüåØ 

This quick and easy recipe can transform a monotonous meal into a zesty feast in no time.

Ingredients: Long-grained rice, Olive oil, Onions, Red bell pepper, Garlic, Jalape√±o, Cumin, Chicken or vegetable broth, Salt and pepper, Chopped tomatoes or tomato sauce.

1. Wash and drain 200g of rice with a mesh sieve. 
2. Heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil in a frying pan. Toss a finely chopped onion, ¬Ω a diced bell pepper, garlic, and a diced jalape√±o in it, and give it a quick saut√©. Simmer for 10 minutes or until the onions become translucent.
3. Toss in the rice and saut√© for 2 minutes, or until it‚Äôs toasted and golden brown. Add ¬Ω a teaspoon of cumin, salt, pepper, 400g chopped tomatoes, and 250ml broth to it. If you‚Äôre using ketchup instead of tomatoes, add it to the mixture. Stir everything together.
4. Bring the mixture to a boil and cover it with a lid. Reduce the heat and simmer for 15 minutes or until the rice is thoroughly cooked.
5. Garnish with chopped cilantro or lime wedges. 

Chef Tip: Mexican rice can be stored in the fridge for up to 5 days. Place it in an airtight container and pop it in the microwave to reheat it, or stir it in a frying pan on the stovetop.

Once you try out this recipe, you won‚Äôt be able to go back to plain rice ever again. Serve it for Sunday dinner, and watch the eyes of your loved ones light up with your praises!

description:
Boquerones arugula salad

So this salad is my first dish I ‚Äòcooked‚Äô (read: chopped) in NYC after my move a month ago, as exploring the city has been wonderful. It is simple, quick, and delicious!

description:
haven't been out as much these days so i finally got my act together and cooked up one of the easy recipes i saw on @geniuseatss ages ago!

SPICY GARLIC BUTTER PASTA
which i paired with some garlic prawns too üòú

i didnt make much (or any) variation other than not adding parmesan (coz im a weirdo and dont the stuff üôà) and i also added in some chilli oil by @hdfoods.au

INGREDIENTS:
- 200g Spaghetti
- Diced Garlic
- 1tbsp of Chilli Flakes (i used dried chillis)
- 2 tbsp soy sauce
- 1 tbsp oyster sauce
- 1 tbsp chilli oil
- 3 tbsp olive oil
- 2 tbsp butter

METHOD:
1) Cook the pasta in a pot of boiling water
2) Fry off the garlic in the oil until golden
3) Add the butter, chilli flakes and sauces
4) Throw in the cooked pasta, chilli oil -  mix and serve!

GARLIC PRAWNS:
i used a pre-pack from @woolworths_au hehehe

description:
Dairy free iced sugar cookies 

Ingredients: 

üíï 250g plain flour 
üíï100g dairy free butter
üíï 100g caster sugar
üíï 1 egg 
üíï 1tsp vanilla extract 

For the icing: 

üíï 200g icing sugar
üíï 4tbsp water 
üíï Few drops of food colouring of choice

Method: 

üíï Preheat the oven to 190C and line a baking tray with baking paper

üíïCream together the butter and sugar until well combined

üíï Beat the egg and add to mixture along with vanilla

üíï Fold in the flour and use your hands to form a dough

üíï Roll out on a lightly dusted surface at a thickness of around 1cm 

üíï Bake for 7-9 minutes, until golden brown 

üíï Transfer to a cooling rack to cool 

üíï To make the icing, sift the sugar into a bowl and stir in water to form icing 

üíï Add a few drops of food colouring and spread the icing over the cookies once cool 

üíï Top with sprinkles if you have them! 

üíï Enjoy! #recipe #easy #easyrecipe #easyrecipes #recipeoftheday #food #foods #foodie #foodies #instagram #instagramers #fyp #fyp„Ç∑ #cookie #cookies #sugarcookies #biscuit #cookiedecorating #cookiemonster #dairyfree #dairyfreerecipes #ambersdairyfree #ambersdairyfreedelights #pink #icing #sweet #instagramfood #aesthetic #delicous #foodblogger

for the icing:

method:

cream together the butter and sugar until well combined

description:
Chicken Sothi

Comfort food has always been what I love the most. It reminds of the amount of love üíï and thought my Grandma üëµüèª puts in when she cooks for us ‚ù§Ô∏è.

(On the plate : rice , chicken sothi, omelette and fish acar)

Ingredients:

1 medium sized onion - diced
4 garlic cloves - chopped 
1/2 inch of ginger - sliced 
1 tomato- cubes
1 red chilli- julienne
120ml of coconut cream
200ml of water (or as required)
1 tbs of oil 
A pinch of carom (ajwain) seeds
1/2 tsp of turmeric powder
1 bay leaf
1 tbs of chopped coriander
Salt to taste
1/4 tsp of crushed black pepper 
1/2 tsp paprika 
200g of chicken (or any meat of choice)

Method :

1. Add oil to the pan; once heated - add in the bay leaf, onion, garlic , and ginger.
2. Once the onions are translucent , add in the tomatoes and chillies. 
3. Add in the chicken when the tomatoes are soft and stir for 5mins.
4. Then add on the coconut cream, water, turmeric powder, carom seeds, black pepper and paprika till chicken is cooked.
5. Once cooked, add salt to taste and chopped coriander. 
6. Enjoy üòç

description:
Afternoon Tea has never looked this good üòã. 
This delicious zesty orange cake will melt in your mouth with every bite. We can‚Äôt think of a better way to get vitamin c üòâ

Happy Baking ‚ù§Ô∏è

Zesty orange cake

Ingredients:
4 large eggs 
1 cup castor sugar
1 cup oil
1 cup fresh orange juice
Zest of oranges used (reserve half for glaze) 
2 cups self-raising flour
2 tsp baking powder

Glaze:
2 cups icing sugar 
70ml orange juice and reserved zest

Method:
1.Preheat oven to 180·µíC.
2.Whisk eggs well until frothy.
3.Add sugar and beat until thick and creamy.
4.Add oil and whisk well.
5.Add half of juice and zest and blend.
6.Sift in flour and baking powder and blend.
7.Add rest of the juice and blend.
8.Bake in a +/- 22cm x 13cm greased, lined baking pan +/- 45 minutes until a skewer comes out clean.
9.Allow to cool.
10.Drizzle over and smooth the glaze over the cake.

Note: Freezes well.

description:
First Day of School called for some homemade Chic Fil A for my kids. For me, Nashville Hot Chicken Sandwich.

Ingredients:
Peanut oil, for frying
1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
1/2 cup cornstarch
1/2 teaspoon baking powder
Kosher salt
1 cup buttermilk
2 teaspoons hot sauce
1 large egg
4 boneless, skinless chicken thighs, patted dry
4 tablespoon Nashville Hot Chicken Seasoning
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1 teaspoon smoked paprika
Lettuce
Mayonnaise

Recipe:
1) Pat Dry Chicken and vacuum seal. Cook Sous Vide 3 Hours at 155. 
2) Pat Dry Chicken and let cool. 
3) Add a scant 1/2 inch of peanut oil to a cast-iron skillet. 
4) Set that over medium-high heat. Meanwhile, set up your dredging station: flour, cornstarch, baking powder, and a pinch of salt in a shallow bowl; buttermilk, hot sauce, egg, and a pinch of salt in another shallow bowl. Whisk each mixture with a fork until well combined.
5) Bread the chicken thighs: First, season the chicken with salt. Now, dredge in the dry mixture, then dunk in the buttermilk, then back into the dry. Fry until golden brown. 
6) While they‚Äôre frying, combine the Nashville seasoning, garlic powder, paprika, and black pepper in a heatproof bowl. When you‚Äôre done frying the chicken, add about 3/4 cup hot frying oil to the bowl with the spices and whisk until smooth. Dunk the fried chicken in the spiced oil. (If it gets too thick at any point, just thin out with a little more hot oil.)
7) Build the sandwiches! Toss the lettuce with a little mayo and a pinch of salt. Slather a bottom bun half with mayo, then layer with pickles. Top with chicken, then lettuce. Slather a top bun half with more mayo, then close the sandwich and enjoy!
.
.
.

description:
Stir Fry Minced Pork

Ingredients:
- Minced pork 250g
- Garlic 3 clove
- Chilli padi 2pcs
- Sweet basil leaf 5g
- Oyster sauce 1tsp
- Rice wine 1tbsp
- Light soy sauce 1 1/2tbsp
- Anchovy powder 1/2tsp
- Dark soy sauce 1tsp
- Sugar 1/2tsp

Method:
- Peel and trim off the bottom of the garlic, then slice it into small pieces.
- Wash and trim off the top of the chilli padi, then slice it into small pieces.
- Heat some oil in a wok, add in garlic and chilli padi. Stir fry till fragrant.
- Add in minced pork and fry till it turns opaque. 
- Add in oyster sauce, rice wine, light soy sauce, anchovy powder, dark soy sauce and sugar. Continue to fry for 30 seconds.
- Add in sweet basil leaves and stir fry for 30 seconds.

DONE~

description:
This Porridge with Pistachio and Chia recipe is a #HubSquad submission from one of our lovely members! It is a warming and spicy whole food-based meal. We suggested increasing the serving size of the oats and milk if you‚Äôre after a more filling brekkie ‚Äì this makes it more aligned to The Plate Model, with 1 serve carbohydrate and 1 serve protein. Adding some fruit such as fresh or frozen berries is also a great way to get a serve of fruit whilst adding a bit of sweetness!

Ingredients:
1 cup oats, rolled
500ml milk, any
1 tbsp chia seeds
¬Ω tsp cardamom seeds
20g pistachios, chopped

Method:
1. Place all ingredients in a pan and bring it to the boil.
2. Reduce the heat and let it simmer for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally until the porridge is thick and creamy.
3. Serve as is or top with fresh berries for a serving of fruit. We've topped ours with raspberry compote, which is raspberries, water and 1 tsp sugar simmered over the stove until it thickens.

this porridge with pistachio and chia recipe is a submission from one of our lovely members! it is a warming and spicy whole food-based meal. we suggested increasing the serving size of the oats and milk if you‚Äôre after a more filling brekkie ‚Äì this makes it more aligned to the plate model, with 1 serve carbohydrate and 1 serve protein. adding some fruit such as fresh or frozen berries is also a great way to get a serve of fruit whilst adding a bit of sweetness!

ingredients:
1 cup oats, rolled
500 ml milk, any
1 tablespoon chia seeds
1/2 teaspoon cardamom seeds
20 gram pistachios, chopped

method:
1 . place all ingredients in a pan and bring it to the boil.
2 . reduce the heat and let it simmer for 6-8 minutes, stirring occasionally until the porridge is thick and creamy.
3 . serve as is or top with fresh berries for a serving of fruit. we've topped ours with raspberry compote, which is raspberries, water and 1 teaspoon sugar simmered over the stove until it thickens.
ingredient_lines: ['1 cup oats, rolled', '500 ml milk, any', '1 tablespoon chia seeds', '1/2 teaspoon cardamom seeds', '20 gram pistachios, chopped']

description:
@suhana_spices 

#Repost @ataleofsauceandspice with @use.repost
„Éª„Éª„Éª
Chicken Karahi 
The perfect and easy slow cooked meal for the winter months. It's full of flavour with minimal ingredients. Give it a try and you won't be disappointed. 

CHICKEN KARAHI 
by @ataleofsauceandspice 

Ingredients:
3 chicken fillets (can use whole chicken pieces too)
‚Öì cup Oil or ghee for cooking 
1 heaped teaspoon ground ginger 
1 heaped teaspoon ground garlic 
1 level teaspoon ground green chillies 
1 teaspoon kashmiri red chilli powder 
1 teaspoon ground cumin 
1 teaspoon ground coriander powder 
Salt and pepper to taste 
3-4 large tomatoes (chopped)
2 Tablespoons thick plain yogurt 
Freshly chopped coriander, lemon wedges and ginger julienne for garnish 

Method:
In a wok heat oil/ghee add the chicken along with ginger, garlic and green chillies paste. Let it cook on high heat till the chicken is slightly browned. 
Add the remaining spices and cook for 2 minutes. 
Add the chopped tomatoes mix and let it slow cook on very low heat till the tomatoes are soft and the oil comes to the surface. 
(Keep staring in between to avoid burning at the bottom).

Once the oil is released add yoghurt mix everything and let it simmer for a minute or two. Garnish with ginger and freshly chopped coriander. Serve hot with a squeeze of lemon hot naan or rotis and more plain yogurt on the side if desired. 
Enjoy. 
Note: You may add more of less tomatoes depending on how much masala you like in your final dish.

description:
Breakfast Scones 

There's nothing quite like the smell of freshly-baked scones straight from the oven. 

These scones are light, fluffy and go down a treat spread with butter. 

INGREDIENTS:
100g self-raising flour
100g self-raising wholemeal flour 
1 tsp baking powder
70g fruit & seed mix 
50g butter
100ml milk 
1 egg 

METHOD:

Preheat the oven to 210¬∞C / 200¬∞C fan.

Sift the flours and baking powder into a mixing bowl and, using your fingertips, rub in the butter until the mixture resembles fine crumbs. 

Mix in the dried fruit and seeds. 

Add the beaten egg and then start to add the milk, mixing with a round-bladed knife or fork until you have a soft dough. You may not need all the milk.

Turn out onto a clean floured surface and knead briefly, then roll out to about 3cm thick. Stamp out your scones using a round cutter. Place on a non stick baking tray and brush the tops with a little milk.

Bake for 12-15 minutes until risen and golden brown. 

#scones #easyrecipes #fruit #tasty #biscuits #simplyscrumptious #sconerecipe #sweet #snack #yummy #quickrecipes #seeds #storecupboard #fruitscones #classic #classicrecipe

description:
Oreo Blondies Recipe üç™‚Å†
‚Å†
You will thank me later once you try this recipe for yourself, but then later curse me because you easily demolished a whole tray! üòÖ‚Å†
‚Å†
Oreos by themselves are a delicious treat, but this Oreo blondie recipe takes them to a whole new level that you just HAVE to try.‚Å†
‚Å†
INGREDIENTS:‚Å†
‚Å†
üç™ 2 1/4 cup plain flour‚Å†
üç™ 1 tsp salt‚Å†
üç™ 1/2 tsp bi carb soda‚Å†
üç™ 3/4 cup vegan butter, melted‚Å†
üç™ 1 cup sugar‚Å†
üç™ 3/4 cup brown sugar‚Å†
üç™ 2 flax 'eggs' (to make 1 flax egg combine 1tbsp ground flaxseed and 3 tbsp)‚Å†
üç™ 1 tsp vanilla extract‚Å†
üç™ 1 1/2 cups Oreos, crumbled ‚Å†
‚Å†
METHOD‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ Preheat oven to 180¬∞. In a small bowl, mix together 2tbsp of ground flaxseed and 6tbsp of water. Put aside and allow 'eggs' to thicken.‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ In a mixing bowl, sift flour, salt and bi carb soda.‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ In a separate mixing bowl, fork mix together melted butter, sugar, brown sugar, flax eggs and vanilla.‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ Add in flour mixture and mix together until well combined. Fold in a cup of crushed oreos.‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ In a prepared rectangle baking tray (baking paper/lightly greased), evenly spread in batter. Top with the remaining oreos and bake in oven for about 25 minutes or until lightly golden.‚Å†
‚Å†
üî∏ Allow to cool in baking tray for a further 10 minutes, and then place on a baking rack until completely cooled before cutting.‚Å†
‚Å†
#cookies #baking #veganbaking #easyrecipes #veganrecipes #easyveganrecipes #bakingrecipes #sweettooth #oreos

description:
No one can argue that pasta nights are the best nights. Especially when the recipe is easy to make and uses seasonal vegetables and herbs. Need some inspiration for dinner? We‚Äôve got you sorted. See recipe below.‚Å†
‚Å†
#PastaNight #SeasonalVeggies #DinnerInspo #HealthyFoods #Dinnertime #EasyRecipes #Nutrition #Health #TheArtahLife #ArtahHealth‚Å†
‚Å†
 _________‚Å†
‚Å†
Mediterranean Artichoke + Brown Rice Pasta ‚Å†
‚Å†
Serves 2 // GF, VE‚Å†
‚Å†
Ingredients:‚Å†
‚Å†
4 handfuls mixed tomatoes, roughly chopped‚Å†
1 jar of artichokes, drained but reserving 2 tbsp oil ‚Å†
2 cloves garlic‚Å†
4 tbsp capers and juices‚Å†
Juice of 1 lemon‚Å†
1 tbsp tomato pur√©e‚Å†
1 tbsp olive oil‚Å†
1 tbsp oregano‚Å†
1 tsp chilli flakes‚Å†
1/2 tsp salt‚Å†
1 tsp pepper‚Å†
-‚Å†
150-200g (1 1/2 - 2 cups) brown rice pasta‚Å†
Large handful parsley, roughly chopped‚Å†
Handful rocket leaves, to serve‚Å†
Drizzle of good quality olive oil‚Å†
1 chilli / to serve, (optional)‚Å†
2 wedges of lemon, to serve‚Å†
‚Å†
Method:‚Å†
‚Å†
1. Preheat your oven to 200¬∞C/180¬∞C fan. Place the tomatoes, artichokes garlic, capers, lemon juice, tomato pur√©e and splash of water in a suitable baking tray, drizzle in artichoke oil and season with oregano, chilli flakes, salt and pepper. Give everything a good mix and bake for 15 minutes until soft and beginning to char.‚Å†
‚Å†
2. Cook the pasta as per in the instructions on the back of the packet. Drain but reserve about an inch of starchy pasta water. Stir in the tomatoes, artichokes and plenty of parsley.‚Å†
‚Å†
3. Serve immediately with some rocket leaves, a drizzle of olive oil, some chilli and wedges of lemon.‚Å†
‚Å†

description:
Easy Recipe: Rice Pilaf ~ SAVE THIS NOW!

A lot of you asked for the recipe. Here it is. If I can do it, so can you!

Ingredients:
- 3 cups long-grained rice (I‚Äôm using basmati), washed and rinsed until clear
- 5 tbsp unsalted butter
- 1 medium onion, minced
- 6 cloves garlic, minced
- 4 1/2 c water
- 1 chicken cube
- 1 tsp ground cumin
- 1 tsp ground turmeric
- 1 cinnamon stick
- 2 tsp salt
- 1/2 tsp pepper
- 1/2 cup dried cranberries
- 1/2 cup pepitas

Steps:
1. Melt the butter on a heavy-set pot like a dutch oven set on medium heat.
2. Add onions until softened. Then add garlic. Cook until a bit golden.
3. Then put in your cumin, turmeric and cinnamon stick. Cook until fragrant.
4. Add in your rice. Stir to make sure the rice is coated with the butter and spice mixture.
5. Pour in your water with the chicken cube. Mix until the chicken cube has melted. 
6. Stir in the salt and pepper. Let it boil.
7. Reduce to low heat. Cover your pot and let it simmer for 15 minutes.
8. Turn off the heat. Add your cranberries and pepitas, cover and let it stand for a few more minutes. Fluff before serving.

description:
This looks absolutely amazing! What do you think? Repost from @lifebyleanna
‚Ä¢
Crescent Roll Taco Ring üåÆ - A fun idea for taco Tuesday! Such an easy dinner idea and I‚Äôm already thinking about what else I can make inside a crescent dough wreath! 

Serve with your favorite taco toppings! I used lettuce, sour cream, tomatoes and cheese! 

Ingredients:
- 1 Pound Ground Beef
- ¬Ω Cup White Onion diced
- 1 Package Taco Seasoning Mix 1 oz
- ¬Ω Cup Water
- 1 Cup Shredded Cheddar Cheese
- 2 Crescent-style Dinner Rolls 8 oz can

Directions:
1. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.
2. Heat a large skillet over low-medium heat. Cook the ground beef and onions until the beef is no longer pink. Drain grease if needed, and return meat to the skillet.
3. Add the water and taco seasoning. Continue to cook until the mixture begins to thicken. Remove from heat.
4. Open both cans of dough, unroll, and separate into triangles. Using a large baking sheet or pizza pan lined with parchment paper, place the wide sides of the triangles in the center with the tips overlapping. The center should form a circle. The longer tips of the triangle will face outward, and the end result will look like a sunburst.
5. Spoon the beef around the overlapping portions of the dough to form a large circle. Top the beef with shredded cheese. 
6. Pick up the outer point of a triangle and lay it over the top of the meat and cheese. Tuck the point underneath the inside of the circle of dough so the meat and cheese is covered. Continue this around the circle until all the outer points are folded over and tucked into the center.
8. Bake for 18 to 22 minutes or until the ring is golden brown. Cut into slices and serve with your favorite toppings.

Recipe by: myheavenlyrecipes.com

description:
Wholewheat spaghetti with courgette, cabbage, chard and broad beans in a lemon and olive oil sauce. Inspired by spaghetti aglio e olio. With mozzarella and homegrown beetroot on toast. A delicious 30 minute 5-a-day #vegetarian #vegetarianrecipes meal! 

Make it #vegan #veganuk #veganrecipes : omit mozzarella on the toast

For 2
Ingredients:
1. 5-a-day components: 1. Courgette, 160 gm. Sliced. 2. Chard, 160 gm 3. Cabbage, 160 gm 4. Baby broad beans (I used frozen), 160 gm 5. Beetroot, spring onions, 160 gm
2. Garlic, 4 cloves, finely sliced 
3. Chilli, 1, finely chopped 
4. Olive oil 
5. Zest and juice of 2 lemons
6. Honey (optional) 
7. Parsley 
8. Wholewheat spaghetti, 160 gm cooked in a big pot of salted hot water
9. Mozzarella (optional) 

Method:
1. Dry fry courgette for a couple of minutes using high heat. Let it take on a wee bit of colour 
2. Reduce flame to lowest and add a tablespoon of olive oil 
3. Fry the garlic and chilli for a couple of minutes. Add the cabbage and steam fry for 5 minutes. Start cooking your pasta now
4. Add the frozen broad beans and wilt in the chard, cook with lid on for 5 minutes. 
5. Add the spaghetti (Al dente) with a splash of pasta water. Keep flame low and add zest and juice of a lemon. Turn hob off and let the pasta soak up all the delicious veggie juices. Make the salads. 
6. Season to taste and finish with fresh parsley and a final drizzle of extra virgin olive oil 

Beetroot salad: as in previous post so grated beetroot, spring onions with some minced garlic, extra virgin olive oil, zest and juice of a lemon, wee pinch of salt (to taste) and a drizzle of honey if you please. 

Make it a #onepotmeal : after step 4, add the spaghetti (use a big, wide pan and don‚Äôt break the spaghetti or you won‚Äôt be able to slurp!) and a cup of water and cook with lid on. Keep an eye and keep adding water a ladle at a time till spags cooked. I think it‚Äôs easier to cook spaghetti separately, just one more pot to rinse off!

#30minutemeals #fiveaday #fiveadaygoals #spaghetti #healthyfood #healthyrecipes #easyrecipes #buonapetito #northumberlandfoodie #newcastlefoodie #ukfoodie #pasta #ukfoodblogger #ukfoodblog #foodblog

‚Äî‚ÄîIngredients:

‚Ä¢ 1 bag of marshmallows

description:
Save my favorite summer dessert --
üçìStrawberry pudding üçì

As much as I don't want to admit it--summer is coming to an end but if you're looking for a dessert to bring to the end of the summer parties, you gotta try this one! I love how light it is and that it's no bake! 

Strawberry Pudding

Ingredients:
1 quart strawberries, washed and drained (Plus extra for garnish)
1 package Cream Cheese at room temperature, 8 oz.
2 containers Whipped Topping 8 oz. each (divided)
1 package Vanilla Wafers
1 package instant vanilla pudding
2 1‚ÅÑ2 cups Milk- enough for pudding recipe.

Directions:
1.In a large bowl slice strawberries. In another bowl mix one container of whipped topping with cream cheese. Mix and set aside for later use.
2. In another bowl combine ingredients for vanilla pudding.
3. Layer bottom of 9x12" glass container with vanilla wafers. Next, layer strawberries, cool whip & cream cheese mixture, then pudding.
4.Top with whipped topping and garnish with extra strawberries

Save this recipe for your next party! 

Share your favorite summer dessert in the comments!!

description:

These are simple and sweet and such an unique flavor.

INGREDIENTS:
1 egg
1/3 cup oil
1 tsp vanilla 
1/3 cup sugar
3 tbsp brown sugar
1 tsp salt
1 tsp baking soda
1 package of sesame powder
1/4 cup oil 
Sesame seeds

DIRECTIONS:
Preheat to 350 degrees
Mix solids
Add in liquids 
Put in fridge for 15 minutes
Take out, roll into balls
Place on tray
Sprinkle sesame seeds
Bake for 17 minutes

description:
You're going to love this recipe! 

Honey-lemon Vinaigrette: 

üçØ Making honey is incredibly resource intensive for a honey bee colony. A worker bee makes 1/12 of a teaspoon of honey during its entire lifetime. It has to consume honey in order to make honey.

üêùKnowing how hard bees work, I strive to use every last drop of honey. When lemon juice is mixed with honey, the acidity of the lemon dilutes the viscous honey, making it possible to get every last sweet drop!

So when I have almost used all of the honey in a jar, I know it is the ideal time to make honey-lemon vinaigrette ~ in the honey jar itself.

Ingredients:
‚ñ™Ô∏è 1-2 tablespoons of honey
‚ñ™Ô∏è 2-3 tablespoons of fresh-squeezed lemon juice from 2 lemons
‚ñ™Ô∏è 2 small garlic gloves, finally chopped
‚ñ™Ô∏è 2 teaspoons whole grain, old style mustard (optional)
‚ñ™Ô∏è 1/2 teaspoon sea salt
‚ñ™Ô∏è Freshly ground pepper
‚ñ™Ô∏è1/3 cup extra-virgin olive oil
‚ñ™Ô∏è 1/3 cup extra-virgin olive oiltional)

1Ô∏è‚É£ Squeeze 2 lemons with seeds removed
2Ô∏è‚É£ Pour lemon juice in honey jar and shake with lid on vigorously to mix the lemon and honey. This will help integrate the honey into the vinaigrette as you add ingredients.
3Ô∏è‚É£ Add garlic, mustard, sea salt, and ground pepper and shake with lid on vigorously again.
4Ô∏è‚É£ When the honey and other ingredients are well-integrated, add olive oil and leaves of fresh thyme. Shake with lid on again. Adjust salt and pepper to taste.
5Ô∏è‚É£ This salad dressing can be used on any salad, mixed vegetables such as grilled zucchini and summer squash or a pasta salad.
6Ô∏è‚É£ Refrigerate between uses. Let come to room temperature and shake vigorously to serve.

Let us know how you like this recipe in the comments!
.

.

description:
Creamy Farfalle w/ Spinach & Sun-Dried Tomatoes üåøüçÉ 

By @janetsmunchmeals

Ingredients:

1/2 lb. farfalle
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped
1 tsp olive oil
3 large garlic cloves, minced
4 plant based sausages (396 g)
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tsp dried parsley
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1 cup (packed) baby spinach
1 cup canned crushed tomatoes
1 cup dairy free heavy cream

Instructions:

Cook farfalle in salted water according to package directions, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water prior to draining.

Meanwhile, preheat large pan on medium heat. Add onions and oil, cook on medium low for 10 min, adding 1/2 cup water to prevent burning if needed and stirring periodically. Add minced garlic and crumble in the sausages. Stir, add all the seasonings, and cook for 6 to 8 min, stirring periodically, until starting to brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 to 3 min, stirring as spinach wilts. Add pasta, stir, add pasta cooking water if desired. Serve with red chili flakes and basil if desired.

description:
CHICKEN ZUCCHINI CASSEROLE
Ingredients:

3-4 boneless skinless, chicken breasts (about 2 Ibs)
1/4 tsp salt
1/4 tsp pepper
1/4 tsp garlic powder
1 medium zucchini
1 medium yellow squash (I used butternut cause it‚Äôs all I had in my garden)
1/2 medium sweet yellow onion
1/2 cup pesto prepared 
4 oz parmesan cheese
4 oz mozzarella
Instructions:
1. Preheat the oven to 375 ¬∞F.
2. Chop the zucchini, squash, and onion and combine
3. In a large casserole dish, lay the chicken in a flat single layer and season it with the salt, pepper and
garlic powder. Next layer the veggies on and then dollop the pesto over the veggies, then top with the
cheeses.
4. Bake on the middle rack for 35-45 minutes or until chicken is cooked through, 165 F internal temp. If it
starts to brown more than desired, loosely cover with foil until it is done cooking
5. Serve hot and enjoy!

Recipe Notes:
You can cut the chicken in half, chunks, or use chicken tenderloins in lieu of full chicken breasts to make serving easier. Cooking time may be reduced. Leftovers can be stored in an airtight container for 3-4 days in the refrigerator or in the freezer for up to a
month.

And yes, there will be a lot of liquid at the bottom, so don‚Äôt get discouraged. 

#chickenrecipes #zuchinni #squash #easyrecipes #freshveggies #zuchinnirecipes #healthyeating #healthyrecipes

description:
Clotted cream biscuits
Ingredients:

 1 tsp baking powder

 1 cup of whipping cream.

 1 egg

 1/2 cup of sugar

 2 cups flour

 1 tablespoon vanilla extract

 Salt to taste

 Process:

 Mix the baking powder with the milk. Mix with the sugar and the egg.

 Add the whipping cream, the vanilla essence and the flour.

 Add a pinch of salt to the preparation.

 Integrate well all the ingredients until obtaining a homogeneous mixture.  Incorporate the milk that we had previously reserved.  Do it little by little so that it mixes well until you obtain a uniform and smooth paste.

 Portion balls of dough and roll them out to the desired thickness.

 Cook the gorditas on a hot comal or griddle over low heat and lightly greased with vegetable oil.

 When the gorditas are browned on one side, flip so they cook on the other.

 Eat hot.

description:
Usually I cook my mushrooms in a pan with olive oil and soy sauce. Decided to switch it up with an oven roasted garlic mushroom recipe!

Ingredients:
Shitake mushrooms
4 tbsp olive oil
1 tbsp white wine vinegar
3 tbsp garlic powder (or more if you want more taste)
2 tbsp minced garlic
1 tbsp salt
Handful of chopped basil or parsley

Recipe:
- Mix olive oil, vinegar, basil/parsley, garlic and salt in a bowl. 
- Add mushrooms to bowl and toss. 
- Toss in extra garlic powder depending on how much taste you want. 
- Put in a dish in the oven for 30 minutes at 425 degrees. 

#mushrooms #garlic #ovenroasted #foodie #easyrecipes

description:
Zoodle Pizza üçï
Soaking up all of the fresh summer produce while we can! We went to @easternmarket today to pick up farm fresh produce, most from @fusilierfamilyfarms96. This zucchini noodle pizza puts a healthy spin on plain old pizza and also is super easy to make vegetarian. 

Ingredients:
4 medium-sized zucchini, spiralized
2 eggs, lightly beaten 
2 cups shredded mozzarella, divided
‚Öì cup grated parmesan
¬º cup all-purpose flour
2 T. cornmeal
8 oz. pizza sauce
¬Ω cup pepperoni (optional for vegetarian style)
1 ¬Ω t. Kosher salt
2 T. fresh basil for topping (optional)

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. In a 9x13 baking dish or foil tray, coat with cooking spray. Place spiralized zucchini in a colander with salt and let sit for 15 minutes. Using a paper towel, squeeze excess moisture out of zucchini. In a medium bowl combine the eggs, 1 cup of mozzarella, parmesan, flour, and cornmeal. Add the zoodles and stir. Transfer mixture to baking dish.
Bake zoodles uncovered for 15 minutes. Next, spread pizza sauce on top of zoodles. Add the remaining mozzarella cheese and the pepperoni. Bake for 20 minutes.
Add basil on top and let the pizza rest for at least 10 minutes.
 Enjoy!! Serves 6-8 

#easternmarket #instafood #instarecipe #healthyrecipes #healthyfood #summerrecipes #summercooking #summerveggies #freshproduce #easyrecipes #foodstagram

description:
LEMON BROCCOLI PASTA 
This is not a pretty picture, but it was gooood! I had this huge bag of broccoli I had to cook, so I needed to make something where broccoli was the main star. I was nervous for this, but my husband loved it!! Indy loved it too minus the broccoli lol. I left it out for her. 

Ingredients: 
Organic Broccoli florets 
@simpletruth4u organic White beans 
Pasta 
Lemon juice 
Optional: bacon, Parmesan cheese 

Instructions: 
Prep broccoli with olive oil, lemon juice and salt.
Roast broccoli in the oven at 400 degrees for 15/20 mins. 
Boil water for pasta. I used @cappellos gluten free.
Drain pasta, but keep about a cup of pasta water in the pot.
Add a cup of lemon juice, salt, a can of rinsed white beans and olive oil to the left over water to make a sauce. 
Add parm cheese to the above if using it.
Add the pasta back in.
Put broccoli on the plate first, then scoop over the pasta mixture so the sauce gets on the broccoli too. 
Add some crumbled bacon on top if you want. You can definitely leave the bacon off. It was still very good w out it. 
Enjoy!

description:
Homemade apple pie DONUTS with maple GLAZE HOLY COW üçéüç© do not wait to make these‚Ä¶ you deserve them this instant! 

DONUT RECIPE
1 3/4 c. flour 
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp baking powder 
2 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp salt 
2 Tbs butter, melted
1 egg, room temperature 
1/2 c. brown sugar 
1/2 c. granulate sugar 
1/2 c. milk 
1/4 c. apple cider, room temperature 

CRUMB MIXTURE RECIPE 
1/4 c. flour
1/4 c. sugar 
3 Tbs. butter, softened 
Sprinkle of cinnamon 

MAPLE GLAZE RECIPE
1 Tbs butter 
1/4 c. pure maple syrup 
3/4-1 c. powdered sugar 
Pinch of salt and cinnamon 

Whisk together dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt. In a separate bowl whisk together remaining (wet) ingredients. Pour dry ingredients into wet ingredients and whisk until just combined. Pour into well greased donut pan, about halfway. 

Cut crumb mixture ingredients together with a fork until crumbles form. Sprinkle crumb mixture on top. Bake at 350 for 10-11 minutes. 

In a small saucepan, melt syrup and butter together. Once melted, remove from heat and whisk in cinnamon, salt, and powdered sugar. Let it rest for a few minutes before drizzling on top of donuts.

description:
SIMPLE ICED MATCHA LATTE üçµ 

THE best summer drink and perfect for those HOT summer days! ü•µ

Ingredients: 
1-2 tsp matcha powder (more or less, your preference) 
Milk of choice 
2 tbsp boiling water
Sweetener of choice: stevia, maple syrup, Manuka honey
1 cup of ice

Directions:
In a small bowl, add the matcha powder. Pour in the hot water and whisk until the matcha has fully incorporated into the water. It should be bubbly with no clumps! 

Add ice to a cup. Pour matcha mixture over ice. Add your milk, and sweetener of choice. 

If you have a milk frother, frothing the milk and adding your sweetener then works amazing as well! 

Matcha is high in antioxidants, which help our bodies fight against free radicals that can damage our cells and cause diseases. It also contains vitamin C, selenium, chromium, zinc and magnesium! ‚ú®

LOVE your live, MOVE your body, NOURISH your soul üå±. 

Recipe by: @nourish.withnicole

add ice to a cup. pour matcha mixture over ice. add your milk, and sweetener of choice. 

if you have a milk frother, frothing the milk and adding your sweetener then works amazing as well! 

matcha is high in antioxidants, which help our bodies fight against free radicals that can damage our cells and cause diseases. it also contains vitamin c, selenium, chromium, zinc and magnesium! 

love your live, move your body, nourish your soul . 

recipe by: .withnicole

description:
Spicy Cucumber Salad, Blue Ribbon Sushi Style 

For those of you who don‚Äôt know me, I LOVE @blueribbonsushi LOVE! LOVE! LOVE! I moved to New York City in 1998. I was 18 & starting university. After I graduated my first apt was around the corner from the original Blue Ribbon Sushi on Sullivan Street in SoHo. I thought I was so cool, 22 & living alone in SoHo. Real SJP Carrie Bradshaw sh*t goin‚Äô down. I use to go to Blue Ribbon all the time. Dine alone at the bar, read my book or magazine, & I had a crush on the manager Bowie.üíö

So here is a shout out to ALL @eatblueribbon restaurants. The Brasserie down the street, the bakery that once was & now all the locations in all the cities. So many great memories & ALWAYS the BEST food. Anyway, enough of my memory lane BS. Truth be told, I ate there the other night, hence the need to recreate this salad that is, yup you guessed it, simple & delicious.ü•íüçãü§ç

Takeaway, you too can make this. I sub yuzu hot sauce from @traderjoes for thier garlic & habanero sauce & it‚Äôs spot on! 

Ingredients:
5 Persian cucumbers, peeled & sliced round 
¬º cup sour cream
2¬Ω tbsp yuzu hot sauce 
Chives, finely chopped
Flaky salt

Directions:
Place your cucumbers in a bowl & set aside. In a small bowl whisk your sour cream, yuzu hot sauce & salt. Then pour over your cucumbers & stir to evenly coat. Add salt to taste, sprinkle your chives on top & serve. 

PS Little Tip(s)‚Ä¶ Little Trick(s)‚Ä¶
‚Ä¢If you want to make more, double the recipe.
‚Ä¢You can use scallions instead of chives.
‚Ä¢You can add minced garlic for an extra kick of flavor. 
‚Ä¢Most importantly, do not be afraid to try new things, even if it seems scary or unattainable, if you put your mind to it you can do it‚Ä¶ trust me I‚Äôm livin‚Äô proof.üí•üíõ

description:
Dhal - a dish made with lentils or other split pulses ‚Å†
‚Å†
Probably one of the simplest Indian dishes you  can cook and healthy and cheap too! ‚Å†
‚Å†
Lentils are high in fibre, and complex carbohydrates, while low in fat and calories. Their high protein, gluten free whicht makes them a perfect option for those on a low carb diet. ‚Å†
‚Å†
This recipe is my go to, and I often change the type of lentils which gives a different texture and flavour to the dish.‚Å†
‚Å†
Rayeesa‚Äôs Dhal ‚Å†
‚Å†
Ingredients:-‚Å†
‚Å†
1cup Red split lentils ‚Å†
¬Ω med onion thinly sliced‚Å†
2/3 tbsp. ghee (or ¬Ω veg oil + butter) to fry onions ‚Å†
1 tsp. turmeric ‚Å†
1tsp. Paprika ‚Å†
2 tbsp. Garlic and ginger paste‚Å†
1 ¬Ω tsp Ground coriander ‚Å†
Salt to taste‚Å†
Green chillies, 2 small ones chopped (optional)‚Å†
Fresh coriander to garnish‚Å†
‚Å†
Method :-‚Å†
‚Å†
Wash lentils thoroughly in clean water‚Å†
(Leave to soak for ¬Ω hr if possible)‚Å†
add turmeric and enough water to cover lentils with approx. 1‚Äú above water‚Å†
Bring to boil and then let it simmer until lentils are cooked and soft.‚Å†
Get a masher to mash the lentils or a large spoon.‚Å†
Add 1 cup water, Green chillies, Paprika, Salt, Ground coriander, Garlic & ginger‚Å†
Let pan simmer for 5-10mins‚Å†
Gently fry onions in oil & butter until golden brown and add to dhal mixture‚Å†
Garnish with fresh coriander and serve!‚Å†
‚Å†
#dhal #comfortfood

description:
EASY BAKED ZITI

Ingredients:
- 2 boxes of rigatoni noodles
- 1 container of ricotta, whole milk
- 1 block of mozzarella cheese, freshly grated
- 1 roll of @jimmydean regular (or spicy) sausage
- 2 jars of tomato basil sauce (using @classico_sauce here)
- 1/2 tablespoon of dried basil
- 1/2 tablespoon of garlic powder
- 1/2 tablespoon of Italian seasoning 

Steps:
1. Preheat oven to 400 degrees
2. In a medium to large pot cook your sausage throughly, add your sauce and seasonings and simmer for 20 minutes
3. In another large pot cook your pasta noodles, adding a decent amount of salt and oil while boiling 
4. Drain the noodles and combine with the sauce, stir 
5. Add ricotta cheese and stir well until everything is creamy and well combined
6. Pour into a baking dish and top with mozzarella cheese 
7. Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly 

#bakedziti #homemade #cooking #cheapmeals #affordable #easyrecipes #pasta #pastarecipe #noodles #new #newrecipe #followformore #foodblogger #blondefoodgod

‚ÄºÔ∏è ùó™ùóîùó•ùó°ùóúùó°ùóö - This is ùòïùòñùòõ your 'average' soup recipe!

üíö This recipe was adapted from a recipe featured in the August 'delicious' magazine. Something I LOVE doing, is adapting recipes into a healthy, balanced meal. I adapted this recipe by adding chicken for protein, more veggies and omitting the parmesan to serve, although this is also fine if you choose to add it. 

üç≤ üí°Healthy food DOES NOT have to be tastless or boring. Remember that recipes can be adapted to become a healthy option. The flavours in this soup were absolutely mouth watering! 

üëá

üçó ùóñùóµùó∂ùó∞ùó∏ùó≤ùóª, ùóñùóÆùóªùóªùó≤ùóπùóπùó∂ùóªùó∂ ùóïùó≤ùóÆùóª ùóÆùóªùó± ùó©ùó≤ùó¥ ùó¶ùóºùòÇùóΩ

‚ú¥Ô∏èINGREDIENTS:
1 tbsp olive oil
1 leek, finely sliced
1/2 fennel bulb, thinly sliced
3 garlic cloves, crushed
1/2 tsp fennel seeds
6 sprigs oregano, or 1 1/2 tsp dried leaves
1 parmesan rind (such a genius way of adding flavour without the fat and calories of cheese)
4 cups chicken or veg stock
500g chicken breast, cut into large pieces
400g cannellini beans, drained
1 zucchini, diced
2 sticks celery, chopped
1/2 bunch silverbeet

üçãùó£ùóÆùóøùòÄùóπùó≤ùòÜ, ùóîùóπùó∫ùóºùóªùó± ùóÆùóªùó± ùóüùó≤ùó∫ùóºùóª ùó¶ùóÆùóπùòÄùóÆ (optional but super delicious and you only need a tsp or two)
40g almonds, toasted
1/4 bunch flat leaf parsley
2 sprigs oregano, or 1/2 tsp dried leaves
juice of 1/2 lemon
40mL olive oil

‚ú¥Ô∏èMETHOD:
1Ô∏è‚É£ Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat. Add leek, fennel, celery, garlic, fennel seeds and oregano and cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes until softened and lightly golden.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Season, add parmesan rind, stock and 1 cup water and bring to a simmer. Add chicken pieces and cook for 10 minutes or until chicken is just cooked through.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Remove chicken pieces and allow to cool slightly. Add zucchini, cannelini beans and silverbeet and stir for 3-4 minutes or until zucchini is just softened. Shred chicken, return to saucepan and stir. 

4Ô∏è‚É£ Meanwhile for the salsa, simply blend together all ingredients in thermomix or food processor.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Remove parmesan rind and serve. Top with salsa if using, and fresh, torn parsley leaves. üòã
