description:
SAUSAGE, MUSHROOM & BRIE EGG BAKE

INGREDIENTS:
- 16 oz mild Italian sausage
- 2 cups mushroom (sliced)
- 1 small red onion (diced)
- 1 clove minced garlic
- 4 cups spinach
- 1 cup brie cheese (cubed)
- 10 eggs
- 1/2 cup milk
- 1 1/2 tsp garlic powder
- 1 1/2 tsp onion powder
- 1 tsp green goddess seasoning (can omit)
- salt
- pepper
- 1 can crescent roll

STEPS:
1. Start by preheating the oven to 350 degrees.  While the oven is preheating, brown the sausage, slice the mushrooms, and dice the onion.
2. Once the sausage is done, set aside and add the mushroom, onion, and garlic to the pan with the grease from the sausage.  Stir frequently until it is all soft and fragrant, then add in the spinach until it is wilted.  Set aside.
3. Next dice up the brie cheese into cubes and also set aside.  Grab a medium sized bowl and add the eggs, milk, garlic powder, onion powder, salt, pepper, and green goddess seasoning.  Mix until well combined.
4. Once everything is has been prepped it‚Äôs time to assemble the bake.  Start by adding the crescent roll to the base layer of a 9 x 12 baking dish.  Next follow with the browned sausage, the saut√©ed veggies, and the brie cheese.  Finally top it all with the egg mixture.
5. Bake at 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes, or until a toothpick comes out clean in the middle.  Serve with avocado and your favorite hot sauce!

Enjoy! ‚ú®

description:
Who doesn‚Äôt love a recipe that is simple and delicious? üíÅüèª‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è

I make this once a week - it‚Äôs enough for dinner 2 nights in a row and both of our kiddos *love* it! üòã

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢2 Lbs Ground Beef (we use 85/15)
‚Ä¢2 Medium Zucchini (sliced & quartered)
‚Ä¢Elbow Pasta (8oz - I use @eatbanza because it‚Äôs gluten free -plus it adds more fiber & protein!)
‚Ä¢Tomato Sauce (8oz)
‚Ä¢Chicken Broth (4 Cups)
‚Ä¢Shredded Cheddar Cheese (1 Cup)
‚Ä¢Mustard (2T)
‚Ä¢Hamburger Seasoning (1T)
‚Ä¢Tobasco (Optional - to taste)
‚Ä¢Salt + Pepper (to taste)

How to Make It:
‚Ä¢pan fry ground beef in a large pot/skillet
‚Ä¢when beef is finished, toss in the zucchini
‚Ä¢once the zucchini is somewhat tender - add in the broth, pasta, tomato sauce, mustard, tobasco & seasonings. 
‚Ä¢simmer until pasta is ready, then fold in the cheese #ewdavid (IYKYK üòÇ)

Makes 6 servings (1 serving is roughly 466 grams)

*Swipe for Nutrition Facts*

Make sure you save this post, follow me for more recipes and comment below if you try this üòç

JOY!
-HP

description:
Lentil & Meatball Soup With Veggies üßÜüç≤ 

Ingredients: 
-1 1/2 Cup Lentils
-1.5 Lb of Ground Beef
-1 Onion 
-1 Large Carrot
-2 Large Celery Sticks
-1/2 Tsp Curry
-1/4 Tsp Turmeric
-1 Tsp Aleppo Pepper
-2 1/2 Tsp Dry Dill
-1/4 Tsp Garlic Powder
-1 1/2 Tbsp Tomato Paste
-1 Egg
-Salt and Pepper to Taste

Preparation: 
Begin by chopping half the onion into very small pieces or grinding it. Start mixing the ground beef, dry ingredients, tomato paste, egg and onion. Boil a pot of water and once it starts bubbling start rolling up the meatballs and throw them in(You can make them as big or small as you want). While the meatballs begin to cook, poor the lentils into a pot and pour water just enough to cover the lentils. Once the meatballs are about more than half way cooked remove them from the pot and keep them on the side. The lentils should also be cooked by this time but you can always check to see. Rinse the lentils. In a different pot add a bit of any kind of oil you prefer and dice the other half of the onion and begin to saut√© it. Dice the celery and carrots and add it to the onion and saut√© together. Once they begin to cook a little , add in the lentils and meatballs and mix. Add about 4-5 cups of boiling water, mix. Season the soup with salt and pepper to your taste, let it come to a simmer and it is ready to be eaten. Enjoy!

2 large onions, chopped
4 spring onions, sliced (be sure to also add the root ends to the soup -- they are extra healing)
2 large carrots, peeled and sliced
3 celery stalks, sliced
12 large garlic cloves, smashed
4 large sticks of wakame seaweed (this can be left out, or replaced with spinach)
1/4 cup chicken bone broth (this can be substituted with chicken stock)
3 cups water
500g boneless chicken thighs, cut into 1-inch pieces
Salt and pepper, to taste
1 cup small pasta

Method:
1. Put all of the ingredients, except the pasta, into a slow cooker.
2. Cook on high for 4-hours.
3. Add pasta and cook for an additional 15 mins or until the pasta is cooked al dente.

NOTE: This soup can be made on top of the stove if you prefer. Follow the directions above, but you will probably only need to cook the soup for about 1-1/2 hours. Then add the pasta until cooked al dente.

description:
I keep coming back to my Sausage ‚Äòrisotto‚Äô for many reasons, it‚Äôs quick, delicious, and full of low carb veg and meat. Good thing I love this dish because I‚Äôll be eating it all week üòÖ
Since I‚Äôm pregnant I‚Äôm adding peas, but if you‚Äôre strict Keto you can easily substitute these for broccoli, or leave them out all together 
.
.
.

.
.
Ingredients: 
2 tbsp butter 
1 tbsp olive oil 
Meat of 6 sausages, removed from the skin
1 onion, diced 
1 bell pepper, diced 
1/2 tsp chili flakes 
1 tsp Italian Herbs 
2 garlic cloves, minced 
250g cauliflower rice 
100g frozen peas 
150g grated mozzarella cheese 
.
.
.
.
Directions: 
1Ô∏è‚É£Heat the butter and oil on medium high, until hot. Add the sausage meat and brown 
2Ô∏è‚É£Add the onion and pepper, cook until soft 
3Ô∏è‚É£Turn the heat down to low. Add the chili, Italian herbs, and garlic; cook until fragrant 
4Ô∏è‚É£Add the cauliflower and peas. Cook until the peas are warmed through 
5Ô∏è‚É£Mix through the mozzarella. Enjoy! 
.
.
.
.
Nutritional Info: serves 4
Calories: 523
Carbs: 10.7g
Fat: 41.3g
Protein: 24.9g 
.
.

.
.
.
.

description:
Are you Ready for the Air Fryer Revolution?

The first thing you need to know about air fryers is that they don‚Äôt actually fry things. Once you place your food in the frying basket, the machine blows hot air to create a convection cooking effect that browns the food. The crunchy texture is similar to what you would achieve by deep frying.

If you Running out the door to be next in line to buy an Air Fryer or already own one, here is a super easy, delicious chicken recipe to try. 
Tender and Juicy Air Fryer Chicken is golden crispy outside and moist and delicate on the inside. 
Bursting with flavor and oh so good! 

Prep Time: 10 mins
Cook Time: 18 mins

Ingredients:
2 skinless chicken breasts
1 Tablespoons olive oil
1 Tablespoon Italian seasoning
1 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon paprika
Salt and Pepper
Optional: Vegetables (brussel sprouts, carrots, green beans)

Method:
Place the chicken in the air fryer basket. Rub olive oil on the chicken.
In a small bowl add the Italian seasoning, garlic powder, paprika, salt and pepper. Rub on each sides of the chicken.
Cook in the air fryer at 200 degrees for 9 minutes. Open the air fryer and flip the chicken. 
Add the vegetables at this point if using. 
Cook for another 9 minutes or until chicken is done.
Enjoy with some spicy rice or garlic rolls.

Stay tuned for more in our Recipe series‚Ä¶
To View Previous Recipes, Download the Crescent Lifestyle APP and find them on the Social Timeline: http://bit.ly/CresLife

description:
Thai Kale Cashew Salad with Lemon-Ginger Vinaigrette ü•ô

Servings: 4
Calories 320, 25g carb, 20g fat, 10g protein.

Ingredients:

Dressing

3 Tbsp. sesame or coconut oil
2 Tbsp. coconut aminos or low-sodium soy sauce
1 Tbsp. raw apple cider vinegar
1/2 tsp. fish sauce
1 tsp. minced fresh ginger
1 large clove garlic, peeled and minced
1.5 tsp. lemongrass paste

Salad

1/8 tsp. sea salt
6 cups kale, chopped (if you don‚Äôt have kale, then you can use romaine lettuce or spinach)
1/2-3/4 medium carrot, peeled and shredded or julienned
1/2 cup shredded red cabbage, very thinly sliced
1/2-1 bell pepper (red or yellow), thinly sliced
1 green onion, thinly sliced
3 Tbsp fresh cilantro leaves, chopped
1/4 cup dry roasted cashews, chopped
Lime wedges for garnish

INSTRUCTIONS

Combine dressing ingredients in a small bowl and whisk well to combine. Set aside.
Place kale in a large bowl and sprinkle with sea salt. Using your hands, massage the kale with a kneading motion until leaves start to wilt and become slightly shiny or wet-looking (about 2-3 minutes). Very important to massage the kale this way! It makes it more tender and less bitter.
Add carrots through cilantro, then pour dressing over all. Toss to combine.
Garnish with chopped cashews just before serving. Serve with lime wedges.

description:
The perfect picnic basket filler. Full recipe below üëá

Ingredients:
- 50g butter
- 6 spring onions, sliced
- 200g jumbo oats
- 150g grated carrot
- 50g almonds, roughly chopped
- 3tbsp mixed seeds, divided
- 150g Dubliner Lighter, grated
- 2 eggs, beaten
- 1/2 tsp salt flakes
- 1/4 tsp black pepper

Method:
1Ô∏è‚É£Pre-heat oven to 200¬∞C/180¬∞C fan/gas 6 and line a 20cm (8 inches) square tin with baking paper. Set aside.
2Ô∏è‚É£In a large mixing bowl, combine the oats, carrot, almonds, grated Dubliner Lighter cheese, salt, pepper, and 2tsp of the mixed seeds. Mix well with a large spoon.
3Ô∏è‚É£Melt the butter in a small saucepan over medium heat, then add the spring onion and cook until butter starts to foam and spring onion softens. Remove from the heat and stir into the dry mixture. Add the beaten eggs and mix well until evenly combined.
4Ô∏è‚É£Tip mixture into the prepared tin, pressing down evenly with the back of a large spoon or spatula. Scatter with the remaining 1 tbsp of the seeds on the top.
5Ô∏è‚É£Bake for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cook in the tin for 10 minutes, then use the paper to lift the flapjack out onto a wire rack to cool completely.
6Ô∏è‚É£Use a bread knife to cut flapjacks into your preferred-sized portions.

#DistinctivelyDubliner #DublinerCheese #Cheese #CheeseLover #RecipeIdeas #FlapJacks #Summer #Picnics #SummerPicnics #FamilyPicnics #FamilyDayOut

description:
* RECIPE POST 

Some days you want to indulge in rich, restaurant-like North-Indian food but then you don‚Äôt want to indulge in the cooking that it calls for! Nahi? üòÇ

This ‚ÄòPaneer in Cashew & Mawa Gravy‚Äô is the answer to your dilemma! It‚Äôs quick to cook, takes less amount of preps and the outcome? ü§§ Words can‚Äôt describe it! You‚Äôll know when you try it!

Some hot sizzling rotis to go with it, and you‚Äôre good to go! 

Here is the recipe: (perfect for the festive season) 

Ingredients:

Paneer 250 grams
Onion 1 medium chopped
Garlic 3-4 cloves chopped
Cashews 15 pcs
Mawa 100 grams grated (50 + 50) 
Cardamom 2 pc whole
Cinnamon stick 1
Cloves 2
Pepper corns 7-8 pcs
Cumin seeds 1 tsp
Tej patta 1
Milk 1/2 cup
Yogurt 1 tbsp
Garam masala 1 tsp (or kitchen king masala)
Salt to taste
Fresh Cream 2 tbsp
Oil
Ghee

Method:

Step 1: 

Take oil in a pan. Add the whole spices (cardamom, peppercorn, cloves, cinnamon) and saut√© garlic and onion in this until soft. Cool down.

Important: Discard the cinnamon. 

Blend into a smooth gravy along with 50 grams Mawa and 15 cashews and a little water. 

Step 2: 

Take ghee in a pan and add cumin seeds and tej patta. Saut√© and add the gravy. Cook for 3-4 minutes before adding 1/2 cup milk and grated Mawa (this part of the Mawa is optional) Again cool for 4-5 minutes on low heat and then add 1 tbsp yogurt. 

Keep cooking while adding the salt and garam masala. Now add the cream and the paneer and cook for 2 minutes. Switch off and serve immediately.

(The gravy thickens as it cools down, so if you want you can add milk and cook a little to reach the desired consistency!)

Do try and let me know in the comments how you like it!! ‚ù§Ô∏è

description:
Bangladeshi Hotel Style Chicken Soup Recipe

Ingredients: 

1. White Bread 2 pcs
2. Warm Milk 2 cup 
3. Cooking Oil 4 tbsp 
4. Ghee/Clarified Butter 2 tbsp
5. Bay Leaf 1
6. Cinnamon Stick 1
7. Cardamom 4
8. Cloves 4 
9. Onion Paste 1 cup
10. Garlic Paste 1 tbsp
11. Ginger Paste 1 tbsp
12. Coriander Powder 1 tsp 
13. Cumin Powder 1 tsp
14. Chicken 300 gm
15. Cashew paste 4 tbsp
16. Salt to taste
17. Green Chili 8-10 pcs 
18. Water 1.5 cup

Instructions: 

1. Blend bread with warm milk.
2. In a pot, add cooking oil, clarified butter, bay leaf, cinnamon sticks, cardamom, cloves, onion paste, garlic paste, ginger paste, coriander powder, cumin powder, and saut√© for 2-3 minutes.
3. Add chicken and saut√© for 5-6 minutes. 
4. Add cashew paste, salt, green chili, and saut√© for 5 minutes.
5. Pour the bread milk and saut√© for another 5 minutes.
6. Add warm milk, water and cook for 20 minutes. 

Ready to Enjoy!

description:
How about
Creamy Mushroom  Chicken Alfredo for dinner
This was so easy to make and it tastes amazing!
Ingredients:
2 skinless chicken breasts, diced
450g fettuccine noodles
2-1/2 cups all purpose cream/whipping cream
5 cloves garlic, minced
1 sm onion, chopped
1 cup champignons/canned mushrooms, optional
1-1/2 cups shredded parmessan cheese
2 tbs butter
salt and white pepper to taste
1/2 tsp ground nutmeg, optional
1 tbs oregano
Method:
Cook fettucine according to package instructions and set aside.
In a large skillet, saute chicken in 1-1/2 tbs cooking oil.
Cook until no longer pink and juices run clear.
Remove and keep warm.
In the same skillet, saute garlic and onions until tender.
Add the champignons/mushrooms and cook for 3-5minutes.
Add butter, salt and pepper, all purpose cream and cheese.
Return chicken to the pan; heat through and until the cheese is melted.
Serve Alfredo sauce over prepared noodles.
Garnished with freshly grated parmesan and parsley if desired.
 enjoy

description:
Strawberry Custard Slices üßÅüç∞üçì

Makes 8
Ingredients:
Jus rol or any brand of pre rolled puff pastry 
250g double or whipping cream
200g ready made custard
Icing sugar
Strawberries halved
 
Method:
Cut the pastry into 8 even slices and bake according to the packets instructions. 
To make the filling whip the cream until it is thick and doesn't drop, then fold in the custard and mix together. Put it in the fridge.
When the pastry is fully cooled cut them in half. Spead a good layer of custard cream over the bottom half of the pastry and place a few strawberries over the cream. Then add the top half of the pastry and dust with icing sugar in a sieve. You can whip some extra cream and put a dollop on top of the finished pastry with a strawberry on top if you like.

description:
Greek Chicken Kebabs üçóüßÖüçÖü´ì

Serves 2
Ingredients:
4 tbsp olive oil divided 
2 tbsp freshly squeezed lemon juice 
1 tbsp lemon zest (optional)
1 tsp paprika
2 tsp dried oregano
2 tsp dried basil
1 tsp dried thyme
3 cloves garlic minced
1 shallot minced
Sea Salt and freshly ground black Pepper 
2lb boneless and skinless chicken thighs cut into one inch chunks
1 red onion
1 red pepper
10 cherry tomatoes halved

Method:
In a large bowl mix 2 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, lemon zest, paprika, oregano, basil, thyme, garlic, shallot, 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp pepper. Stir in the chicken and mix it well. Leave for at least 2 hours but preferably leave overnight.

Thread the chicken onto the skewers. Brush on each side with the extra 2 tbsp olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Grill or bbq them. I chose to bbq them, they can be grilled on medium heat. Turn them though out cooking either way you cook them. 

I combined chopped red onion, chopped red pepper and cherry tomatoes and olive oil and salt and ppper and cooked them on the bbq in a bbq wok. Serve immediately with hummus or tzatziki sauce and heated pitta breads. I used @dunnesstores lemon and coriander hummus.

description:
Mutton chops with gravy

Ingredients:
600g mutton or lamb chops (about 8 chops)
6 green chillies
4 red chillies
3 slices ginger (each 1cm or in thick)
5 cloves garlic
2 tbsp plain yoghurt or juice of 1 lime
2 tbsp coriander (ketumbar) powder
1 tbsp chilli powder
2 onions-chop
4 tomatoes - chop
6 stalks coriander leaves - chop
salt to taste

Ingredients for frying
1 small onion - slice thinly
4 cardamoms
5 cloves
1 stick cinnamon 5cm (2 in) long
10 tbsp oil

4 cups water

Method:
Blend the green chillies, red chillies, ginger and garlic
In a large bowl, combine chops with all the ingredients except ingredients for frying, oil and water. Heat oil, add
ingredients for frying. When fragrant, add mutton and fry till fragrant then add water. Cover and boil, removing cover and stirring from time to time. Continue cooking till mutton is tender and the gravy is very thick.

Chicken 400 g

Pepper ¬æ tsp
Salt 1 ¬º tsp
All-purpose Flour ¬Ω cup
Cornflour ¬Ω cup

Method:

description:
Potato - mushroom scones with cheese and green onion feathers
For a long time, I wanted to make something like this to show once again that we can eat potatoes, and this does not harm our weight.

Ingredients:
üî∏1 Egg
üî∏500 g Potatoes (fresh, peeled)
üî∏150 g Mushrooms (champignons)
üî∏ 40 g Flour (I use corn flour)
üî∏ 40 g Onion green feather
 üî∏90 g Processed cheese (3x 30 g)
üî∏ 8 g Oil
üî∏ Salt, pepper

Preparation:
1 Peel the potatoes and cook until they are soft. Drain the excess water and grind/blend them into a porridge. Cool it.

2 Finely chop the mushrooms and fry in a pan with spices.

3 To the cooled potato porridge - add eggs, onion, flour, salt, pepper, and fried mushrooms at the end, and knead a homogeneous dough. Divide the dough into 6 equal parts.

4 Make scones - put 15 g of processed cheese in the middle of the puree. Repeat with all six scones.

5 Put a little oil in a pan and fry for 5 minutes on both sides.

description:
Quick and Easy Piyali Fish Recipe

Ingredients:
 
1. Piyali Fish 200 gm
2. Cooking Oil 3 tbsp
3. Onion 1 cup
4. Coconut Paste ¬º cup
5. Red Chili 1 tsp 
6. Turmeric 1 tsp 
7. Coriander 1 tsp 
8. Salt to taste
9. 2 Lime Leaves
10. 5 green chilies 
11. Fresh Coriander 1 tbsp

Instructions: 

1. In a frying pan, drizzle cooking oil with chopped onion, coconut paste, red chili, turmeric, coriander, salt, and lime leaves.
2. Add piyali fish and mix well. Garnish with green chilies.
3. Cook for 5 minutes on medium heat and garnish with fresh coriander.
4. Cook for another 15 minutes on low heat. 

Ready to Enjoy!

description:
üåÆRecipe Ôøºfor Nacho Dip

Ingredients:

2 ounces cream cheese, softened
2 teaspoons Kitcheneez Taco Seasoning
6 ounces shredded Mexican-blend cheese (1 1/2 cups), divided
1 (15 oz) can black beans, drained and rinsed
1 (15 oz) can corn kernels, drained
1 (14.5 oz) can diced tomatoes, drained or 2 ripe tomatoes, chopped
1 (4-ounce) can chopped green chiles
Topping options: diced tomatoes, diced avocado, sour cream, fresh or pickled jalape√±os, fresh cilantro leaves
Tortilla chips, for serving

Directions:

Preheat oven to 350*.
Place the cream cheese into a bowl. Add Kitcheneez Taco seasoning and 1/2 cup of the shredded cheese. Mix well.
Add black beans, corn, tomatoes and green chilies. Stir to combine.
Pour into an 8 x 8 baking dish. Spread evently and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 20-30 minutes or until heated through then broil for 1-2 minutes until the cheese bubbles. Top with desired toppings and serve with tortilla chips.
Top with desired toppings and serve with tortilla chips.

description:
Haven‚Äôt cooked a nice meal for myself at home in so long. It‚Äôs been busy and spending the afternoon in the kitchen just hasn‚Äôt been an option, or I just haven‚Äôt had the energy for it. Honestly, we‚Äôve done more in the last month then we‚Äôve done in the last 3 years it seems! Since coming back from our honeymoon, I‚Äôve slowly been easing myself back to my daily routine and habits, like starting to go on some small runs again, seeing friends, doing the sauna, etc.

Chris is away for the weekend so I decided today was going to be all about me üòà I spent my Saturday at the market, the library, the beach and the kitchen, and now I‚Äôm just about to sit down and have a romantic dinner date with myself ü•∞

This is a yam and cherry tomatoes tart with sage and goats cheese. I imagine you can change the produce with the seasons; pumpkin and broccoli for the fall sounds good!

Ingredients:
Pie crust (I had some in my freezer that I‚Äôd made earlier)
1 cup ricotta cheese
6 eggs
1 large yam, peeled cubed
1/2 cup sliced cherry tomatoes
Goat cheese, broken into pieces to sprinkle on top
Sage leaves, to sprinkle on top
Salt and pepper

Preheat oven to 400. Roast your yams and bake your crust for 20 minutes or until golden. Place eggs, ricotta, tomatoes and salt and pepper in a bowl, whisk to combine. Remove the crust and yams from the oven, place the yams on the crust then pour mixture overtop. Top egg mixture with goats cheese and sage. Bake for another 25 minutes.
.
.
.
.
.
.

‚Å£
Try this very versatile quinoa salad that is nutritious, tasty and can be prepared in less then 10 minutes. Add any seasonal vegetables and whiz up a quick dressing like our famous green dressing or an easy one such as apple cider vinegar, mustard, lemon and olive oil or hummus/ pesto üòã‚Å£
‚Å£
I made a large bowl of this that gave me three servings then added in some extra protein such as chicken, boiled eggs, lean meat or beans üòã‚Å£
‚Å£

‚Å£
‚úîÔ∏è1 cup quinoa, rinsed¬†‚Å£

‚úîÔ∏è1/2 cucumber, chopped¬†‚Å£

‚Å£

1 Tbsp olive oil or extra virgin olive oil, plus more for drizzling

2 cans (15oz-450grams each) chickpeas, rinsed and drained

description:
Chicken Tandoori 

Cut the chicken breast into cubes and the garlic finely.

Place the chicken breast in a bowl with the following ingredients: lemon juice, garlic, curry powder, paprika powder, ground coriander, cumin, chili flakes, grated ginger, pinch of cinnamon, pinch of clove powder and mix.

Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil, the Greek yogurt and salt to taste.
Mix well and let the chicken marinate in the refrigerator (at least 1 hour or longer).

Chop the onion and fry it in a large frying pan with some olive oil.

Then add the marinated chicken and fry until done.
Serve the tandoori chicken with a little Greek yogurt on top or possibly some finely chopped fresh coriander. 

Delicious with a fresh salad or some vegetables and rice and/or naan bread. Enjoy your dinner!

description:
Persian Cranberry Walnut Rice made with goodness of nuts . Healthy yet tasty recipe‚ù§Ô∏è made using mild and sweet California Walnuts from @californiawalnutsindia .
.
A must try rice dish‚ù£Ô∏è
.
Ingredients:
California Walnuts :  8-10 piece
Onion: 1 sliced
Dried Cranberry : 1 tbsp 
Ghee - 1 tbsp
Pre cooked rice : 1 cup 
Spices salt, turmeric, red chilli powder , black pepper powder . 
Spring onion greens 
Lemon juice 
.
Recipe :
1. In a pan add ghee and saute sliced onions till lightly brown .
2. Add dried cranberries ,5-6 chopped california walnuts and saute . 
3. Add pre cooked rice, 1 tsp salt , 1/2 tsp red chilli powder , 1/2 tsp black pepper powder, 1/4 tsp turmeric powder and mix.
4. Cover for 2 mins on low flame , garnish with spring onion greens and add lemon juice as desired ! 
.

description:
Tomato, garlic and Italian sausage sauce with fresh basil and broccoli üçÖüßÑ

Fragrant, healthy, quick and satisfying!

Make this vegan or vegetarian by not adding the Italian sausage!

Ingredients: ü•ìü´ë
-1 red capsicum chopped 
- 1 Italian sausage (spicy or mild) cut into bite sized pieces 
- 2 fresh tomatoes diced
- 1 bunch of basil
-  1 small bunch of broccoli florets 
- 4 garlic cloves finely chopped
- 1 red onion chopped
- 1 jar of red wine and garlic pasta sauce
- Italian herbs mix

Method: ü•¶
1. Add a drizzle of olive oil into a pan with the onions and garlic. Fry until translucent.

2. Add tomatoes, capsicums, and broccoli. Add Italian herbs and cook on a low temperature for 20-30 minutes. The longer you cook the richer the flavour develops.

3. Meanwhile in a separate pan, fry the Italian sausage until brown with olive oil. 

3. Then add the pasta sauce and turn the heat down until low to cook for a 5 minutes until the broccoli has softened.

4. Once the vegetables in the sauce have fully cooked- add the Italian sausage and basil leaves. Stir for a few minutes over low heat.

5. Serve with your favourite pasta and Parmesan cheese!

description:
Who knew making a Dhaba style Masala Pav would be this easy üòã
Get your Dhaba curry paste from the link in our bio

Masala Pav Recipe:
Oil - 1 tsp
Cookd Dhaba Curry Paste - 1 Packet
Capsicum (finely chopped) - ¬Ω Cup
Water - 2 tbsp
Pav Bhaji Masala - ¬Ω tsp
Coriander Leaves (finely chopped) - 2 tbsp

Other Ingredients:
Butter - 1 tbsp
Pav - 4 nos
Onion (finely chopped) - ¬º Cup + ¬Ω Cup
Coriander Leaves (finely chopped) - 2 tbsp + 2 tbsp
Grated Cheese
Lemon Wedges - 2 nos (for serving)

Cooking Instructions:

1. Heat oil in a pan and add the Cookd Dhaba curry paste. Saute it for 1 minute to heat it up. 
2. Add capsicum and saute for 2 minutes. 
3. Add water and continue to cook for 2 minutes. 
4. Add coriander leaves and pav bhaji masala & mix. Remove the masala from the pan. 
5. In the same pan, melt some butter. Cut the pav in half horizontally and toast it, with the cut side down. 
6. Turn the pav and toast the other side on low heat. At this point, add some of the prepared masala on one side of the pav. 
7. Add onion, coriander leaves and grated cheese. Cover the pav and remove it from the pan. 
8. Add more masala on top, followed by grated cheese, onion and coriander leaves. Serve with a lemon wedge.

description:
This Hawaiian Macaroni Salad is a magnificent side dish for all the cookouts and picnics or for family dinner night! ‚ú® 

Save this post! Full recipe below! üëá

Ingredients: 

1/2 lb dry elbow macaroni
1/4 cup onion, minced
2 TB shredded carrots
1 cup real, whole mayo
1/4 cup green onion, thinly sliced
1/2 tsp white pepper
1 tsp kosher salt
Optional: freshly chopped parsley for garnish

Instructions: 

Bring a large pot of well salted water to boil. Cook macaroni until tender, according to package instructions. Drain, rinse thoroughly with cold water; be sure to drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients with the cold, cooked macaroni. Toss to combine well. Chill 2-3 hours or overnight. Toss again right before serving.

description:
Tomato, tomahto! üçÖüçÖ It doesn't matter how you say it, all we know is this blistered tomato ravioli recipe is perfecto. Turn your summer harvest into pure perfection with this Blistered Tomato Ravioli Recipe below.

Blistered Tomato Ravioli Recipe
Yield 2 servings
Ingredients:
1 package cheese ravioli
2 pints Wild Harvest organic grape tomatoes
3 cloves garlic, minced
2 tablespoons Wild Harvest organic olive oil
3-4 tablespoons Wild Harvest organic basil, sliced into ribbons
1 teaspoon salt
1 teaspoon pepper

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 400¬∞
2. Place tomatoes in a small bowl and toss with garlic, olive oil, salt and pepper.
3. Lay tomato mixture on a parchment lined baking sheet. Bake for 15-17 minutes or until skins are blistered.
4. While tomatoes are cooking, prepare ravioli according to package instructions.
5. When tomatoes are blistered, remove from oven and add sliced basil. Toss to combine.
6. Top cooked ravioli with tomato basil mixture and additional olive oil if desired.

description:
Whip-It Up Wednesday!

Chicken Bacon Ranch Spaghetti Squash Casserole üòã

ONE recipe your whole family will love & our clients do too. I love healthy recipes that the entire family can enjoy TOGETHER!

Recipe: 
Serves 6

Ingredients:
2 lbs boneless skinless chicken breast, cooked and cubed
4 cups zucchini ‚Äúnoodles‚Äù or spaghetti squash
4 slices lean turkey bacon, cooked and chopped up
3 cloves garlic, minced
1 cup unsweetened almond or cashew milk
¬æ cup reduced-fat Ranch dressing
2 cups reduced-fat Mexican Cheese blend
1, 4 oz can green chilies

Instructions:
1. Chop your chicken into bits.
2. Mince your garlic cloves.
3. Preheat the oven to 350.
4. Keep a small bit of your bacon drippings in the pan. Cook the garlic cloves (don‚Äôt brown). Toss in the chicken and cook for about 1 minute mixing it all together. Dump in the milk and ranch. Mix over medium/low heat for about 2-3 minute until slightly thickened.
5. Add in 1 cup of cheese. Mix EVERYTHING all together thoroughly. Then fold it in with the noodles. Get it all mixed up together. At this point you can add the green Chile and bacon too.
6. Dump the casserole in a large casserole dish. Pour the remaining cup of cheese over the top of the casserole. Cook for 15 minutes at 350 until cheese is nicely melted.

Per serving
1 leaner
1 fat
1 1/2 greens 
1 condiment

To make this a complete lean and green meal, you could always increase the veggies to 6 ¬Ω cups OR serve with a side of another steamed veggie (such as broccoli; ¬æ cup per serving needed)

description:
One of the things we talk about often when it comes to healthy eating for those of us over 50 is making sure we get enough protein. üí™

One of the best ways to do that is to find ways to incorporate it into our snacks. üòã 

Today we‚Äôre sharing one of our favorite ways to do that: Apple Pie Protein Energy Bites!
The beauty of it is that not only are they good for your body their good for the taste buds too. 

So much so the only real issue is not eating them all in one sitting 

These little delites are only about 45 calories each so you can have 2 or 3 and get a nice does of protein (10-15 grams) as you go about your day. 

Give‚Äôem a try and let us know what you think below! 

 üçè Apple Pie üçè Protein Energy Bites (makes about 15) 

 Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1 cup Apple Pie Filling (Look for No Sugar Added Pie filling)
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup unsweetened cashew milk (or almond)
‚Ä¢ 1 tsp powdered Stevia, or to preferred taste
‚Ä¢ 1 ¬Ω tsp ground cinnamon, or to preferred taste
‚Ä¢ 3/4 cup Vanilla Protein Powder
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup Instant Oats

Directions::
‚Ä¢ In a food processor, blend together the apple pie filling, milk, stevia, and cinnamon. Carefully pour in the protein powder and oats, and mix until completely incorporated. 
‚Ä¢ Line an airtight container with wax paper or parchment paper.
‚Ä¢ Roll the mixture into a ball in your hand and place it in the container.  Ideally you should get about 15 balls. Of course you can make them bigger or small if you choose. 
‚Ä¢ Once rolled, transfer the protein ball to an airtight container, and refrigerate until ready to eat! 

Follow us for even more super delish yet healthy recipes!

description:
EASY ORANGE AND CINNAMON WAFFLES üçäüßá Who wants to dig in? They make a delicious breakfast, snack, or brunch, and they‚Äôre vegan and gluten-free too! 

Ingredients:
1 cup Pancake Waffle Mix Original Iswari
1 cup almond plant-based milk
Zest of 1 orange
1 teaspoon of cinnamon
2 tsp poppy seeds

Preparation:
- Place all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well with the help of a wire rod, until obtaining a homogeneous mass.
- Place small portions of dough in a waffle maker at room temperature medium, and let it cook for about 3 minutes.
- Repeat the process until all the dough is finished.
- Serve with slices of orange, kiwi, and hemp seeds

description:
Over 100 Delicious Vegan recipes. Plant based recipes for muscle growth fat loss and a healthier lifestyle
Visit my website in bio!!!

Squash Blossom Vegan Quesadillas! üåÆ

Alexa from @alexafuelednaturally created this incredible dish! Check out her recipe below:

RECIPE
Ingredients:
Corn tortillas
10 squash blossoms
Avocado
Salsa
Salt & pepper

"Tofu cheese"
1 (14 ounces) container medium firm or extra firm tofu
2 tbsp olive oil
Juice of 1 lemon
2 tbsp any plant milk (I used oat milk)
1/2 tsp salt
4 tbsp nutritional yeast (I like Trader Joe's brand)
1/2 tsp garlic powder

Instructions:
1. Remove tofu from package and wrap tofu block in 2 paper towels. Squeeze for 10 seconds then break apart tofu into your food processor. To the food processor add salt, 2 tbsp olive oil, lemon juice, nutritional yeast and garlic powder, plant milk. Pulse 6-10 times until you reach the consistency of ricotta cheese like consistency. Taste and adjust salt and seasonings as needed.

2. Clean off each squash blossom with a damp paper towel then trim the stems. In a pan over medium heat, add a tiny bit of oil and quickly cook the squash blossoms 10 seconds on each side. Season with a little salt and pepper.

3. Warm a cast-iron skillet or pan over medium heat. (Optional tip my mama taught me... wait till pan is super hot then quickly dip tortilla in water and add to hot pan. If the pan Doesn't sizzle then it's not ready!!!* flip the tortilla 10-15 seconds later...This makes your tortillas SO SOFT and fresh tasting giving a dry tortilla the moisture it needs. *** only do this tip w/ corn tortillas not flour tortilla***

4. Add a generous spoonful of tofu cheese on half the tortilla, then add squash blossom then fold over. Let cook for 1 minute on both sides.

5. Add sliced avocados and serve with salsa!

description:
In the words of Bob Ross ~ ‚Äúwe don't make mistakes, just happy little accidents.‚Äù üé®

I needed to make use of some over ripe bananas & came across the banana bread cookies recipe by @mainlymonica on @deliciouslyhealthysweets ‚Ä¶ I didn‚Äôt have a few of the ingredients listed so I altered the recipe and made it my own! Safe to say these banana oaty cookies are my new fave & I‚Äôll be adding them to my morning yoghurt bowl for the foreseeable - the perfect chewy oaty texture, like a flapjack granola!üòç

Ingredients:
* 250g ripe banana
* 100g Peanut butter 
* 100g 0% Greek yoghurt 
* 150g @thegreatbritishporridgeco blueberry & banana porridge oats (KG10 for 10% off)
* 80g @freesoulsistas vanilla protein powder 
* 20g maple syrup 
* 1tsp baking powder 

Instructions:
* Preheat oven to 170c & have a lined baking tray set aside

description:
A little hearty zesty treat coming your way this recipe wednesday! Today‚Äôs Low-carb Pasta with Lemon Chicken features Shirataki Noodles. I mean, lemon chicken?? a little zesty surprise for your meal! Head on down to see the recipe, that‚Äôs good for 3!

LOW-CARB PASTA WITH LEMON CHICKEN

INGREDIENTS:

- 2 (200G) packages shirataki noodles
- 1 lb. pastured chicken breast, cut into bite size pieces
- 1 tablespoon¬†MCT Oil¬†or other cooking oil
- 1 large clove organic garlic, minced
- ¬Ω teaspoon dried oregano or 1 teaspoon minced fresh oregano (leaves only)
- ¬Ω teaspoon Himalayan pink salt
- 1 large lemon, zested and juiced (keep zest separate from juice)
- 2 tablespoons grass-fed butter or ghee
- 1 tablespoon¬†Collagelatin,¬†or other grass-fed gelatin
- 1-2 tablespoons fresh oregano to finish (leaves only)

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Prepare shirataki noodles according to package instructions (rinse for 15 seconds, then boil for 2 minutes in a pot of boiling water, then drain the noodles and place them in a dry skillet (no oil) over medium heat and ‚Äúdry roast‚Äù them for 1 minute). Set aside.
2. Heat a large cast iron skillet to medium-high heat and add oil.
3. Add chicken, garlic, dried oregano and Himalayan pink salt to skillet and cook for approximately 8-10 minutes or until fully cooked stirring occasionally. Remove chicken from skillet leaving and set aside.
4. Lower heat under skillet to medium and add lemon juice to deglaze pan. Next add butter and stir until melted. Then whisk in Collagelatin to finish.
5. Add noodles and chicken back to skillet and toss to combine.
6. Serve topped with lemon zest and a garnish of fresh oregano.

‚Üí RECIPE LINK: https://www.bulletproof.com/recipes/low-carb/low-carb-pasta-lemon-chicken-recipe-3g2x/

#keto #shirataki #shiratakipasta #pasta #pastarecipes #chicken #lemon #lemonchicken #recipes #chickenrecipes #yummy #healthy #healthyrecipes #food #ketorecipes

description:
Kung Pao cauliflower‚Å£
By¬†@woon.heng¬†üî• Perfect over some steamed rice for a delicious meal! Recipe below

‚Å£Ingredients:‚Å£
1 small head cauliflower, wash & cut into florets‚Å£
1 small green bell pepper, cubed‚Å£
1/2 small red onion, cubed & 2 cloves garlic - sliced‚Å£
1/4 cup dry roasted cashews‚Å£
4 dried Thai chilis/red chilis‚Å£
oil for frying and cooking‚Å£
‚Å£
Batter ingredients: Mix 3/4 cup all-purpose flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, a few shakes of white pepper in a bowl with 1 cup of cold water until well combined. The batter should be on the thicker side.
Dip cauliflower florets in batter, shake off excess & fry until golden brown. (I used a small saucepan) Drain excess oil on a paper towel. (Bake version: grease a baking sheet pan with oil, place battered cauliflower florets on the pan. Bake at 485F until light golden brown for about 20-25 mins, be sure to flip halfway & brush a florets with oil, if needed. For the last few minutes, you may broil to get a crispier texture) ‚Å£Sauce ingredients: Mix together 1/2 tablespoon dark soy sauce, 1/2 tablespoon sugar, 2 tablespoons soy sauce & 1 tablespoon Chinese cooking wine/sherry in a bowl & set aside.‚Å£
‚Å£
In a heated nonstick pan with 1 teaspoon oil, sauteÃÅ onion, garlic, bell pepper, dried chilis until fragrant. Add sauce and cook mixture for 10-15 seconds. Then, add cauliflower florets, cashews, and coat cauliflower well with the sauce. .

description:
Thai Style salmon.

This recipe is fast and easy and it is also very appetizing.ü•∞

INGREDIENTS:
- 2 skinless salmon fillets (always go for good quality and not farm one)
- 200gr Thai Jasmine rice
- Chilli flakes, to taste
- Ginger powder, to taste
- 1garlic clove, crushed
- 2 tbsp Miso paste
- 2 tbsp Fish sauce
- 150gr Shiitake mushrooms, sliced
- 250gr pak choi
- 100gr fresh leaf spinach
- 1 lime
- Sesame oil.

METHOD:
Cook the rice in some salted boiling water according to packet instructions.

In a large pan heat the oil (over medium heat), add the chilli, ginger and garlic and cook for a few minutes. Add the Miso paste and fish sauce as well as 300ml of hot water.

Stir and cook for 5 minutes.

Add the salmon and mushrooms, cover, simmer for 10 minutes until the fish is cooked.

Meanwhile steam the pak choi and spinach for 5 minutes approximately.

Serve the salmon with the veggies, the rice and some lime wedges.

#thaisalmon #salmonrecipes #shitakimushrooms #fishrecipes #trytastyflavours #homemadefood #fishmaincourse #healthyrecipes

description:
.
BLUEBERRY & BANANA MUFFINs
by Eat For Wellness

Ingredients: 
4 ripe bananas (mashed)
1 cup fresh or frozen blueberries
1/2 cup Extra Virgin Olive Oil 
2 eggs 
1/4 cup brown sugar 
1 teaspoon bicarb soda
1 ¬Ω teaspoons baking powder 
2 teaspoons cinnamon 
1/3 cup plain natural yoghurt 
1 1/2 cups plain wholemeal flour 
1/3 cup self-raising flour

Method: 
1. Preheat oven to 180¬∞C (160¬∞C fan-forced). Line sixteen 80ml (1/3-cup) capacity muffin tins with paper cases. 
2. In a large bowl, beat sugar and oil with an electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs and beat well.

3.Sift wholemeal flour, self-raising flour, baking powder, bicarb soda and cinnamon in a separate large bowl. 

4.Combine wet ingredients with dry ingredients and fold in the yoghurt, mashed bananas and blueberries. Spoon mixture into lined muffin tins. Bake for 20 minutes or until a skewer inserted into the centre comes out clean. Set aside to cool. Serve muffins warm or at room temperature. . 

Created by Vicki Foord (Accredited Practising Dietitian and Sports Dietitian)

description:
A unique and delicious soup that is surely to warm you up on a cool winter night. It‚Äôs spicy, creamy and protein-loaded. Spicy Carrot & Peanut Butter Soup is a recipe by Kerry Locatelli. Thanks @nuzest_nz¬†üòçüòçüòç 

‚ÄãINGREDIENTS:
‚Äã
üç≤ 1kg Carrots 
üç≤¬†2 Tbsp Avocado Oil or Olive Oil
üç≤¬†1 Onion
üç≤¬†4 Cloves Garlic
üç≤¬†¬Ω Cup Peanut Butter
üç≤¬†2 Tbsp Kaitaia Fire Chili Sauce
üç≤¬†2 Tbsp Chopped Basil
üç≤¬†1 Serve Just Natural Clean Lean Protein
üç≤¬†1 Litre Vegetable Broth/Stock 
üç≤¬†400ml Coconut Milk
‚Äã
‚ÄãDIRECTION:
‚Äã
1. ‚ÄãPeel and roughly chop the carrots. 
2. Place them in an oven tray, drizzle with 1 tablespoon avocado oil and roast in the oven at 180C for about 30 mins. 
3. Slice and then fry the onion in a large pot with a tablespoon of avocado oil. 
4. Add the garlic and saute. 
5. Once the carrots are roasted, add to the onions and garlic, cover with the vegetable broth and bring to the boil. 
6. Turn the heat down and add the peanut butter, basil and Kaitaia fire. 
7. Allow this to simmer for about 5 mins. 
8. Add the coconut milk and Clean Lean Protein. 
9Blend the soup with a handheld stick blender or carefully in batches in a blender.

‚ÄãEnjoy!
‚Äã

#peanutbuttersoup #spicysoup #healthyrecipes #soup #nuzestnz

description:
Veggie pasta
üïØ loadshedding friendly 

I love this pasta, I chuck in whatever veggies I have lying around. 

- roast butternut (if electricity)
- slow cook tomatoes / I generally air fry on low heat for a while, alternatively fry on stove top.
- fry lots of garlic in lots of olive oil, towards the end add in chopped broccoli ü•¶ be careful not to burn
- (if the kids arent eating I usually add chilli flakes) 
- use whatever veggies you want- spinach is also a goodie.

- cook your pasta
- chuck all your veggies in.
- finely chop a packet of mint and flat leaf parsley, toss in just before serving. 

Dish it up. I like to top with avo and goats cheese. And a swirl of olive oil- But totally optional. 

Key ingredients: lots of olive oil, garlic, mint and parsley. If u have those you good to go üëçüèºü§úüèº

Great served the next day for work lunch too.

description:
Tagliatelle with a lemon-garlic-zucchini pesto sauce. Light summer lunch.
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶.
Ingredients:
- 1 middle-sized zucchini (enough pesto for two portions)
- tagliatelle pasta
- 1 clove of garlic
- juice of half a lemon 
- pine nuts
- parmesan 
- salt and pepper to season
- olive oil
‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..
1. Wash and coarsely grate the zucchini. Fry gently in pan with a tablespoon of olive oil and the crushed clove of garlic for five minutes.
2. Cook the tagliatelle according to the packaging.
3. Add the tagliatelle to the zucchini, add the lemon juice and two tablespoons of the pasta water and mix together.
5. Serve with pine nuts and parmesan.

Recipe idea from @bbcgoodfood (without the prawns and with pine nuts and parmesan)

description:
Berry Delicious Vegan Amaranth Breakfast Bowls! Sometimes the simplest breakfast is the best. That can certainly be said of this delicious recipe that takes the creamy smooth texture of cooked amaranth, the super-grain full of fiber and clean nutrition, and couples it with fresh fruit and subtle hints of spice in a coconut milk confection. It's absolute heaven.  It's easy for any day of the week and the amaranth can be cooked in a rice cooker.  Make it ahead and it is a quick re-heat for busy mornings.

Ingredients:

3 cups Water
1 cup Organic Grains Amaranth (http://ow.ly/5TNs50KfrM0)
 1/2 tsp Salt
 2 cups Fresh strawberries
1 cup Fresh blueberries or blackberries
Agave nectar
¬Ω cup Coconut milk
1 tsp Cinnamon
¬Ω tsp Ginger
1-2 Tbsp. Orange zest (1 orange)

Cook the Amaranth

1 cup amaranth
3 cups water
salt to taste (I use about 1 tsp)

Directions:  Combine water and salt in a 1 and a half quart (6 cups) capacity heavy pot with a tight-fitting lid and bring to a boil. Add the grain, cover the pot, and turn the burner to the lowest setting.
Cook covered without stirring for 25 minutes. 

Vegan Breakfast bowls:

To the cooked amaranth pot add ¬Ω cup agave, ¬Ω cup coconut milk, 1 tsp cinnamon, ¬Ω tsp ginger, zest of 1 orange. Divide between 4 bowls. Top each bowl with ¬Ω cup sliced strawberries, ¬º cup blueberries and a drizzle of agave. Enjoy.

#Vegan #breakfast #amaranth #grainbowls #easymeals #organicfood

description:
Broccoli & Bacon Creamy Pasta ü•¶ü•ì
This meal was so yummy and only took 30 minutes.

Ingredients: 
2 heads Broccoli 
450ml Thickened Cream
3Tbs Vegeta
8 Strips of Streaky Bacon sliced 
Spiral pasta or pasta of your choice
Grated Fresh Parmigiano Reggiano 
2Tsp Paprika 
Chilli flakes optional

Method:
1. Boil your broccoli and pasta both in salted water in seperate pots. Cook your pasta 1-2 min under the recommended time as we will finish it in the sauce.
2. Grate your parmesan and slice your bacon while the broccoli boils.
3. Fry off your bacon in a pot till the fat renders and it crisps up on the edges, season with salt and pepper ( don‚Äôt drain the fat it help will season the sauce )
4. Remove your broccoli from the water and cut how you like, I liked small florets for this dish, then add it to the pot with the bacon and fry off for a minute. Then add a few tablespoons of pasta water along with your Parmigiano till it melts.
5. Add your thickened cream to the pot, I did about 450ml for 3 servings. I then add salt, pepper, paprika, & vegeta chicken seasoning.
6. Add your drained pasta to the sauce pot and mix well, let everything cook together till your pasta has finished cooking.
7. Serve with chilli flakes & extra parm on top ‚ò∫Ô∏èü´∂üèº

#cooking #pastarecipe #easymeals

Kosher salt and freshly ground black pepper

3/4 pound ground Italian sausage, casing removed

1 cup part skim ricotta cheese

1/3 cup freshly grated Parmesan

1 large egg

1/4 cup chopped fresh basil leaves

2 cloves garlic, minced

Line a baking sheet with paper towels. Lay zucchini slices flat in a single layer onto the prepared baking sheet. Sprinkle each side with 1/4 teaspoon salt; let stand 15 minutes.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.

Spread 1 cup marinara sauce sauce onto the bottom of a 1o-inch oven-proof skillet; set aside.

description:
#halloweenvibes üéÉ PUMPKIN SOUP WITH ROASTED CHICKPEAS ü•£

Ingredients: 
- pumpkin (I use 1 big pumpkin or 2 small pumpkins for this recipe)
- 125g chickpeas - canned/cooked 
- 3 x 10g olive oil
- 50g onion
- 30g garlic

1. Preheat the oven to 200¬∞C.
2. Peal the pumpkin and scrape out seeds then cut the pumpkin in to chunks.
3. Add olive oil, salt and pepper to the pumpkin chunks and stir.
4. Place pumpkin chunks on to a tray lined with baking paper and bake for 15 minutes.
5. Preheat olive oil in a pot and stir-fry the onion and garlic. 
6. Add baked pumpkin chunks and add water so it covers in pumpkin. Cook until the pumpkin is soft.
7. Meanwhile add olive oil and spices to the chickpeas and stir.
8. Bake chickpeas on 200¬∞C for 30minutes.
9. When the pumpkin is cooked use a stick blender to blend the pumpkin mixture. You can remove a bit of water before blending and add it later if needed. 
10. Serve the soup with roasted chickpeas.

üìùNutrition information
100g = 62,8kcal
Fat: 2,7g
Carbohydrate: 6,8g
Protein: 1,9g 

Enjoy!

description:
I love the convenience and ease of meals like this. Be sure to screen shot or save this recipe to make you life healthier and easier! These are super to pack in a cooler and take down on the beach or to the lake! 

Cheeseburger Mason Jar Salad

4 servings 
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp ground black pepper
‚Ä¢ ¬Ω cup thinly sliced cucumber
‚Ä¢ 4, quart-sized mason jars
‚Ä¢ 1¬º lb. 90% lean ground beef
‚Ä¢ 6 tbsp lemon juice
‚Ä¢ 8 cups chopped leaf lettuce
‚Ä¢ 4 oz. reduced-fat, shredded cheddar cheese
‚Ä¢ ¬º tsp salt, divided
‚Ä¢ 2 scallions, chopped
‚Ä¢ 1 cup diced fresh tomatoes
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup water
‚Ä¢ ¬º cup white vinegar
‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp yellow mustard

Directions: 

1. Heat up a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Spray pan with non-stick spray.

2. Add ground beef and brown all sides, breaking up any clumps; season with salt and pepper. Drain and allow to cool.

3. Bring vinegar, water, and a pinch of salt to a boil. Pour liquid over cucumbers and set aside to make pickles. Drain the juice when ready to serve.

4. Whisk together the mustard and lemon juice to make a vinaigrette.

5. For 1 portion, fill a quart-sized mason jar with 1¬Ω tablespoons of lemon mustard vinaigrette, ¬º cup of tomatoes, 4 ounces cooked ground beef, 2 tablespoons of pickles, 2 cups lettuce, 1 ounce of shredded cheese, and ¬º of the scallions. 

For our clients on program, this breaks down to:
1 lean - 3 greens - 0 healthy fats - 3 condiments (per serving)

description_preprocessed:
i love the convenience and ease of meals like this. be sure to screen shot or save this recipe to make you life healthier and easier! these are super to pack in a cooler and take down on the beach or to the lake! 

cheeseburger mason jar salad

4 servings 
ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 1/4 teaspoon ground black pepper
‚Ä¢ 1/2 cup thinly sliced cucumber
‚Ä¢ 4 , quart-sized mason jars
‚Ä¢ 11/4 pound 90 % lean ground beef
‚Ä¢ 6 tablespoon lemon juice
‚Ä¢ 8 cup chopped leaf lettuce
‚Ä¢ 4 ounce reduced-fat, shredded cheddar cheese
‚Ä¢ 1/4 teaspoon salt, divided
‚Ä¢ 2 scallions, chopped
‚Ä¢ 1 cup diced fresh tomatoes
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup water
‚Ä¢ 1/4 cup white vinegar
‚Ä¢ 1 tablespoon yellow mustard

directions: 

1 . heat up a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. spray pan with non-stick spray.

2 . add ground beef and brown all sides, breaking up any clumps; season with salt and pepper. drain and allow to cool.

3 . bring vinegar, water, and a pinch of salt to a boil. pour liquid over cucumbers and set aside to make pickles. drain the juice when ready to serve.

4 . whisk together the mustard and lemon juice to make a vinaigrette.

5 . for 1 portion, fill a quart-sized mason jar with 11/2 tablespoon of lemon mustard vinaigrette, 1/4 cup of tomatoes, 4 ounce cooked ground beef, 2 tablespoon of pickles, 2 cup lettuce, 1 ounce of shredded cheese, and 1/4 of the scallions.

description:
NUTRITIOUS BEAN AND SAMP SOUP

Ingredients:
1/2 cup beans
1/2 cup samp
5 cloves
5 all spice
Salt & pepper to taste
1 large carrot
1 large onion
1 cup soup celery
1 potato
Bone marrow/soup meat

Instructions:
Soak beans and samp overnight. (not always needed)
Rinse samp and beans and cook in 4 cups boiling water with marrow bones cloves and all spice. Boil until beans are soft. Add water when needed. Boil for about 1.5 hrs

Add your veg (chopped, grated or blended) and salt and pepper (to your taste) with 2 cups boiling water on medium to high heat.
Keep lid ajar to prevent soup from cooking over!

*add some turmeric, ginger and cayenne pepper for thay extra immune boost!

Enjoy!
#healthymeals #healthybody

fullName: S O L O V Y  K I T C H E N
description:
FIT INTO YOUR BIKINI TAHINI
Ingredients: 
1/2 cup tahini
Juice of 1/2 lemon
1 tbsp of olive oil
cold water
Salt and Pepper 
Dried Parsley

Romaine
Tomatoes
Persian cucumber 
Pine nuts 
Sliced Almonds 

Directions:
Finely chop all veggies for the salad. The key to great lettuce is a thin chop. Bunch the leaves together tightly and chop!! Make sure you pat dry after rinsing or it will get soggy. 

For the dressing: combine tahini, olive oil, and lemon juice. Stir! It will be thick. Slowly pour small amounts of very cold water till the tahini thins out while constantly stirring with a spoon or fork. Keep adding water till you get the consistency you desire. Then add in your parsley, salt, and pepper. Pour on top of your salad and enjoy.

description:
Celebrate this Raksha Bandhan with desi homemade Gajar Halwa sweetened naturally with stevia by Stevi0cal.

Ingredients:
1 kg grated carrots
1 litre milk
250 grams mawa
2 teaspoon stevia by Stevi0cal
2 tablespoons ghee
1/2 cup dry fruits
1/2 tablespoon cardamom (elaichi) powder

The recipe:
1. Heat milk and grated carrots in a Kadhai and bring it to boil.
2. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
3. Add Stevi0cal, elaichi powder and dry fruits to the above mixture.
4. Stir continuously for 5 to 7 minutes.
5. Add ghee and mawa. Fry and stir on low heat until ghee starts separating.
6. Garnish with additional dry fruits.
7. Tastes best when consumed hot.

Happy Rakshabandhan!

#RakshaBandhan 
#HappyRakshaBandhan2022 #IndiaAt75 #RecipeOfTheDay #GajarHalwa #SteviaRecipe

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã

‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã‚Äã

description:
This delicious and crispy biscotti is the perfect cookie to accompany your morning cup of coffee or tea!üòç‚òïÔ∏è
Ingredients:
2 cups all purpose flour 
1 tsp baking powder 
1/4 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp cinnamon 
1/2 tsp vanilla extract 
1 cup granulated sugar
1 cup crushed almond and pistachio 
3 eggs
For chocolate ganache:
1 cup chocolate chips
1/2 tbsp coconut oil
1/2 cup crushed almond and pistachio 
Method:
 - Mix the dry ingredients in a stand mixer, then add the liquid ingredients and mix well until combined 
 - When the dough is formed, add the crushed nuts and mix again 
 - Then put parchment paper in a large tray and transfer the dough
 - Shape the dough into a rectangle with 1/2 inch in height, in the middle of the tray without the edges of the dough touching the tray
 - Bake in a preheated oven at 350¬∞F for 27 minutes
 - Then let it cool for 10 minutes and start cutting into loaves
 - Then spread the biscuits in the tray and bake again at a temperature of 300¬∞F for 15 minutes
 - Then flip the biscuits over and put them back in the oven for 15 minutes
 - Then let it cool completely
 - Melt the chocolate with the coconut oil in the microwave for 30 seconds, repeating and stirring until melted
 - Dip the biscuits in the chocolate, then sprinkle some crushed nuts and place in the fridge until set

description:
I recently discovered pickled mushrooms üçÑ‚ù§Ô∏è

So I incorporated them into a new dish! üë©üèª‚Äçüç≥ Sambal crumb baked cod, pickled mushrooms and cucumber ribbons, with yuzu dashi rice üçö 

You can buy your cod at the link in my bio, and get 10% with code SUMMER10. Recipe below üëá 

Ingredients:
2 cod portions, skin removed

Crumb:
50g dried breadcrumbs 
1-2 tsp sambal 

Pickled mushrooms:
125g oyster mushroom, thinly sliced
70g shiitake, halved or left whole if small
1 tbsp light soy
1 tbsp dashi
1 tbsp mirin
2 tbsp rice vinegar

Pickled cucumber:
120g cucumber (approx 1/2) sliced into ribbons
2 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tbsp mirin
1 tbsp dashi
1 tsp sea salt
2 star anise 

Yuzu dashi rice:
140g brown sushi rice
475ml dashi
Yuzu juice 
Knob of butter 
1/2 red chilli, finely chopped
Salt
Zest of 1 lime

1. Measure out the sushi rice, wash and leave it to soak for 30 mins.
2. Heat the sambal into a frying pan, add the breadcrumbs and mix until well coated. Leave to cool, then blitz to a fine crumb and set aside.
3. Mix all the ingredients for the pickled mushrooms in a bowl and set aside in the fridge for 1 hour
4. Use a potato peeler to slice 1/2 a cucumber into ribbons, then mix with the remaining ingredients and set aside in the fridge. 
5. Drain the rice and place into a pan with the dashi. Bring to the boil, cover with a lid and reduce the heat. Simmer for 40 minutes, then turn the heat off and leave for 10 minutes with the lid on.
6. Pre-heat the oven to 200¬∞C fan. Season the cod with salt and olive oil, then spoon the sambal crumb on top, pressing down to make a crust, bake in the oven for 12-15 mins.
7. Once the rice is cooked, stir in the butter, yuzu juice, 1/2 the lime zest, and chopped chilli.
8. Remove the cod from the oven, spoon the rice between two plates and arrange the pickled mushrooms and cucumber around it. Place the cod on top and finish with an extra zest of lime.

description:
SUMMER FARRO AND GRILLED PEACH SALAD

Have you ever grilled fruit? The flavor is incredibleüçë

Save and share this tasty recipe for a tasty, seasonal salad and follow¬†@ketonic.usa ¬†for more.

Join me for the summer of 1000 salads ü•óThis beauty is sweet, tangy, fresh and filling. The grilled squash and peaches taste amazing. You need to try itü§ò

Ready in 30 minutes
Serves 5
Ingredients
1 8oz bag farro
4 tbsp Mint chopped
3 tbsp basil chopped
2 avocado peeled and chopped
1/4 red onion slivered
1 cup cherry tomatoes halved
2 Persian cucumbers chopped
1/2 tsp salt
pepper to taste
2 tbsp olive oil
2 lemons juiced
1/2 cup artichoke hearts diced
3 cups salad greens of choice for serving
1 goldbar squash cut in half lengthwise for grilling
2 peaches halved and pit removed for grilling
Marinade ingredients:
1 tsp olive oil
Pinch salt
Pinch smoked paprika
1 tsp dijon mustard
Instructions:
1. Cook farro according to package, rinse, cool and set aside in a large bowl
2. Mix Marinade for grilling in a small bowl then coat gold bar squash and peaches with marinade. Grill for 5 minutes each side then let cool and chop
3. Add cucumbers, tomatoes, avocado, onions, artichoke hearts, squash and peaches to bowl with farro
4. Add lemon, olive oil, salt, pepper and herbs and mix well
5. When serving make a bed of your favorite salad greens and top them with the farro salad. I used greens and herbs from my garden!

description:
Recipe: Snickerdoodle Cookies

I rarely bake with friends but always love when I do! My childhood friends Lauren & Audrey requested to make snickerdoodles, so I had to get my favorite recipe from my friend @alldayhuang. These are the perfect fluffy, soft cookies. She‚Äôs letting me share her recipe, so give it a try! The only modification I made was decreasing sugar, as always (her recipe uses 400g (2 cups) of sugar). 

Ingredients (for about 66 cookies):
- 488g (3¬æ cups) all-purpose flour
- ¬Ω tsp baking soda
- ¬Ω tsp cream of tartar
- ¬Ω tsp salt
- 227g (1 cup) unsalted butter 
- 300g (1¬Ω cups) sugar
- 2 large eggs
- 60g (¬º cup) milk
- 1 tsp vanilla
Cinnamon sugar: 
- 3 tbsp sugar
- 1 tsp ground cinnamon

1. In a large bowl, combine the dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, and salt. 
2. In a stand mixer, beat butter for 30 seconds. 
3. Add the sugar and beat until fluffy. 
4. Add eggs, milk, and vanilla, beating until well combined.
5. Add dry ingredients, beating until well combined. 
6. Form dough into 1-inch balls and roll them in the cinnamon sugar mixture. 
7. Place balls 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet; flatten slightly with the bottom of a drinking glass.
8. Bake at 375¬∞F for about 8 minutes or until lightly golden.
.
.
.
.
.

description:
Tomato and Mascarpone pasta üçù (serves 1 if you like your pasta saucey)

Ingredients:
Tomato and Mascarpone sauce 
Whole wheat Fusilli 
1/2 onion (red or white)
2 cloves of garlic 
Vegetables that need using up! (I used baby plum tomatoes and peas)

Method:
Put pasta on and cook according to instructions. Mine took about 13mins. Make sure to salt your water! Some say like the sea but I only do a few twists of my salt.

Finely dice your 1/2 onion (see third photo for size) and saut√© until fragrant and translucent.

Then add your vegetables to also saut√©.

Chop/mince your garlic and add them vegetables are almost cooked.

When the garlic is fragrant and lightly browned, add a portion of your sauce (mine was about 1/2 the pot).

Add some pasta water to the sauce as it cooks.

Check pasta and when done, drain and add to the sauce.

Mix for about 1min on a medium heat and then serve up! 

Salt and Petter to taste!

For those who want to know, this came to about 500kcal but I always round up when adding it all together! There are many ways to bulk this up (with protein) or make lower calorie (with a tomato and basil sauce instead).

description:
Nothing is better than waking up to the sound of rain and having a delicious cheesy breakfast with a hot cup of tea üòç

Check out the recipe here ‚¨áÔ∏è

Cheese Potato Bread baked in frying pan

‚úîÔ∏è Ingredients: 

*Switz Puff Paratha
*2 tablespoons mayonnaise
*1 potato (medium size)
*Mozzarella cheese
*Honey
*butter for frying
*Oil
*Garlic powder
*Red chilli powder 

üìå Recipe: 

1- Take the paratha out of the freezer and let it thaw.
2- Boil the peeled potato for about 20 minutes.
3- After the potato is finally boiled, start mashing it in a bowl and add the mayonnaise, garlic powder and red chilli powder to it and mix well until the mixture forms a soft texture.
4- Take a piece of the Switz Paratha and add a handful of mozzarella cheese, then add a good portion of the mashed potato mixture. Add another layer of mozzarella cheese on top of the mashed potato mixture.
5- Add another layer of the paratha on top, and start sealing it from the side until it is fully closed.
6- In a pan, melt a small cube of butter on medium heat, then fry the paratha on both sides till golden brown.
7- Take out the paratha and start cutting it evenly.
8- Serve with honey dipping sauce or any preferred dip of your choice

description:
üåü  ùëµùíÜùíò ùë©ùíçùíêùíà ùëπùíÜùíÑùíäùíëùíÜ! üåü

Summer = aubergines!üòè most of the recipes I know with aubergines are ùê¨ùêÆùê©ùêûùê´ ùê©ùêöùêúùê§ùêûùêù ùê∞ùê¢ùê≠ùê° ùêüùê•ùêöùêØùê®ùê´ ùêöùêßùêù ùêßùê®ùêÆùê´ùê¢ùê¨ùê°ùê¢ùêßùê†, and this is one of them! üëåüèº

This pasta sauce is called Norma, it originated in beautiful Sicily, and it's made of 3 key ingredients: aubergines, tomatoes and grated cheese! Yes, another so simple yet so nice dish üòÅü•∞

This version includes a final baking step in the oven to get that gorgeous crust on top for extra crunch! ü§©

The super easy method: 
1.  Dice the aubergines and cook in little oil until tender.
2. Add the tomato sauce and keep cooking for a few minutes.
3. Cook the pasta of choice until al dente. Turn the grill/oven on.
4. Mix the pasta with the sauce and add some grated cheese (ideally salted ricotta, alternatively a good pecorino will do). Adjust seasoning.
5. Transfer to an oven dish, cover with more cheese and bake until golden. Enjoy! ü§óü•∞

Tap the link in bio for the full recipe & method, and to get many more easy & delicious italian recipes! Buon appetito! ü§©

1. Season strip steak 30 minutes prior to grilling, let it sit out until it comes to room temperature.

INGREDIENTS:
Pulled Beef:
2 Lbs roast beef
1 Tbsp worcestershire sauce
2 Tbsp olive oil
1 Tsp onion powder
1 Cup beef broth
1 Cup water
1/4 Tsp black pepper
Kosher salt

Teriyaki Sauce:
1/3¬†Cup brown sugar
1¬†Cup¬†soy sauce
2¬†Tbsp¬†rice vinegar
1/2¬†Tsp fresh ginger¬† finely minced 
2 Cloves garlic, minced
1 Tbsp sesame oil
1 Tbsp honey
3¬†tablespoon¬†cornstarch
1/4¬†Cups water

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. In a small bowl mix onion powder, pepper and salt. Rub the mixture over the roast.
2. Drizzle olive oil in instant pot and sear roast beef well from all sides until browned.
3. Pour beef broth, water and worcestershire sauce on top of beef. Set the instant pot to pressure cooker. Cook on high for 60 minutes.
4. Meanwhile prepare the sauce, whisk water and cornstarch in a small bowl. Set aside.
5. In a medium saucepan over medium heat, add oil, soy sauce, vinegar, honey, brown sugar, ginger and garlic. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and simmer for 3 minutes. Add cornstarch and water mixture whisking constantly until the sauce thickens. Set aside.
6. Once the beef is ready, transfer the roast to a platter and shred with 2 forks into chunks.
7. Drizzle teriyaki sauce on top of beef and enjoy! Best served with veggie stir fried noodles or short grain rice.

INGREDIENTS:
2 Lbs salmon fillet, skin on
5 Cloves garlic, minced
1/2 Cup honey
1/4 Cup soya sauce
2 Tbsp olive oil
1 Tbsp butter
Kosher salt and pepper 

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. In a small bowl whisk in honey and soya sauce and set aside.
2. Heat olive oil in a medium skillet over medium-high. Place salmon skin side down and season with salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes covered.
3. Meanwhile add butter to a small saucepan. Add garlic and saute for 30 seconds until fragrant. Add honey and soy mixture and cook for 2-3 minutes until sauce begins to thicken.
3. Pour sauce on salmon and reduce heat to medium. Cook covered for 10 additional minutes or until fish is fully cooked. Serve hot.

3 Cups taiwan cabbage, finely sliced

1/2 Cup red onions, finely chopped

description:
avocado quesadillas
Ingredients:

 2 corn tortillas

 1 large avocado

 100 g low-fat melting cheese

 Pico de gallo to accompany (optional)

 Salt and ground black pepper to taste

 Preparation

 Cut the avocado and add the pulp in a bowl, mix with a little salt and ground black pepper to taste for flavor.  You can add a few drops of lemon to prevent it from turning dark.

 Heat the tortillas on a griddle on both sides and place a little of the cheese to taste on each one.  Let it gratin a bit.

 Serve and place the avocado on top, fold in half and accompany with pico de gallo or your sauce to taste if you want to add extra flavor.  Enjoy some delicious avocado quesadillas, delicious and super easy to make.

description:
carrot croquettes

 Ingredients:
 5 small carrots
 2 beaten eggs
 100 gr of turkey ham
 50 g of wheat flour
 1 cup of
 ground bread
 oil for frying
 Preparation
 Wash and peel carrot, grate into fine strips, mix with diced turkey ham and ¬º cup breadcrumbs.

 Culinary tip: you can add some protein such as tuna to give greater consistency to the preparation.

 With clean hands, form the croquettes and then go through flour, beaten egg and the rest of the breadcrumbs.

 Heat a frying pan with enough oil and fry the croquettes for about 3-4 minutes on each side or until they turn golden brown.  Carefully remove and drain excess fat with absorbent paper.

 Serve to taste with a salad garnish or your favorite complement, enjoy these delicious carrot croquettes, bon appetit!

description:
Corn pancakes Ingredients: 4 corn
 4 clear
 4 yolks
 4 tablespoons grated mozzarella cheese
 1 tablespoon finely chopped coriander
 1 small onion, finely chopped
 1 sweet bell pepper finely chopped (Substitute 1/4 jalape√±o if you want them hot)
 2 tablespoons of breadcrumbs
 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour
 pepper to taste
 Salt to taste Shell the corn and cook in a pot with 2 cups of water, about 10 minutes or until soft.
In a bowl, beat the egg whites until letter point is reached.  Then, incorporate the yolks, beat with your electric device for 30 seconds so that they are well integrated.  Place the cheese, onion, breadcrumbs, flour, cilantro and paprika in a large bowl, stir a little and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain the corn kernels in a colander, add them to the bowl, stir well until the ingredients are evenly distributed and free of lumps.
Add the beaten eggs, stir once more, using a spatula with smooth and enveloping movements so that the eggs retain the air they have acquired.
In a non-stick frying pan, heat a splash of oil, trying to cover the entire surface.  Add 2 tablespoons of the preparation per pancake (This is just a suggestion, add the amount depending on the size you want the corn pancakes), give it a circular shape.
Let cook for approximately 2 minutes over medium heat, turn and fry for another 2 additional minutes on the other side.
Line a container with kitchen paper, place the corn and cheese pancakes on top to remove excess oil.  Serve hot accompanied by hot sauce or other dressing of your choice.

description:
Deviled Eggs ü•ö 
Last night I made my first batch of deviled eggs and my husband couldn‚Äôt get enough of them. I made some mistakes along the way and decided to give it a go again this morning and I‚Äôm so happy with how these ones turned out. Here‚Äôs how I made them‚Ä¶ my super simple recipe - 
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 12 Eggs ü•ö 
‚Ä¢ 3 Tablespoons of Mayonnaise 
‚Ä¢ 1 Tablespoon of Spicy Brown Mustard
‚Ä¢ Ground Black Pepper to taste
‚Ä¢ Sprinkle of Paprika 
Instructions:
Boiled a dozen eggs for 20 minutes in a large pan and then transfer them to an ice bath. Allow them to cool for 15 minutes. Cut your eggs in half and scoop the yellow portion out into a medium sized bowl. Then add mayonnaise, mustard, and ground black pepper to the bowl. With a fork mix up the ingredients until creamy. Top your eggs off with paprika. I find it easiest to sprinkle it on with my fingers.

description:
Quick tea for a hot day ü•µ
Chilli peanut noodles.
Ingredients: (serves 2)
2 spring onions 
30g dry roasted peanuts 
100g sugar snap peas
250g diced chicken breast (or meat free alternative) 
1 clove garlic
1 small piece of ginger 
2 wholewheat noodle nests 

For the sauce: 
1 tbsp sriracha sauce
1/2 tsp chilli flakes 
1 1/2 tbsp honey
2 tbsp soy sauce 
2 tbsp water
1 tbsp vegetable oil 
1 1/2 tbsp peanut butter 
1 tbsp rice vinegar 

Mix all of the sauce ingredients together in a bowl until combined, set aside until later. 

Pop noodle nests into a pan of boiling water and cook per instructions on the pack. (Ours were 6-8 minutes) 

While noodles are cooking, grate garlic and ginger and add to a pan with splash of vegetable oil and diced chicken breast. Cook for 5-6 minutes until chicken is starting to brown

Add sugar snap peas and cook for further 3-4 minutes until starting to soften and chicken is cooked through. 

Once chicken and noodles are cooked, add the sauce to the pan with the drained noodles and give everything a good mix. If sauce is looking a little sticky add a splash of water from cooking noodles. 

Top with sliced spring onions and a sprinkling of roasted peanuts, enjoy!

description:
SALMON, BUTTERNUT SQUASH, SWEET POTATO AND KALE BAKE || ü•¨ 

Something easy and super healthy to make and tastes sooo good! üòç managed to put this together for my hubby‚Äôs birthday ü•≥ this is something that I will keep making because it‚Äôs just so convenient, and can try and add in more veggies too! üòç

Ingredients:
2-4 salmon pieces 
1 medium butternut squash (cubed)
1 medium sweet potato (cubes)
Kale (shredded/chopped - I just bought a bag that was already shredded üòÇ)
1 tbsp rice bran oil (or oil of your choice)
1 tsp Cajun
1 tsp paprika
1 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp turmeric 
1/2 tsp Himalayan salt
1/2 tsp black ground pepper
1/4 tsp rosemary (for the salmon) 

Method:
1) Preheat the oven to 200C and line a big oven dish/tray with baking paper
2) Mix oil and all spices together (apart from the rosemary) in a bowl and toss thoroughly with the butternut squash and sweet potato. Place on the baking tray and bake for 20-25 minutes until soft
3) Take the tray out of the oven, turn over the butternut squash and sweet potato and add the kale. Place the salmon pieces on top and season with salt, pepper and rosemary 
4) Place the tray back in the oven to cook for another 20-25 minutes or until the salmon is cooked through (it should be flaky and check that it is piping hot inside!)
5) Serve immediately. Feel free to have this with some extra salad ü•ó
6) Enjoy! ü§©

description:
Feelin peachy about this recipe üçë These PEACH PASTRY SQUARES made it all of 24 hours in our house before they were gone hahaha
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ Puff pastry 
‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp peach jam 
‚Ä¢ 1/3 cup cream cheese 
‚Ä¢ 1 peach, sliced 
‚Ä¢ 1 egg 
‚Ä¢ Brown sugar & cinnamon to taste
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä
Directions:
‚Ä¢ Lightly flour a work surface and rest 1 puff pastry sheet on top to bring to room temperature. 
‚Ä¢ Sprinkle top of puff pastry sheet with flour and roll out. Use a pizza cutter or knife to cut puff pastry into 6 even squares/rectangles. Use a sharp knife to draw lines ~1 inch from the edges of the puff pastry pieces. 
‚Ä¢ Mix together jam and cream cheese and spread onto puff pastry inside lines. Layer peach on top of cream cheese mixture. 
‚Ä¢ Make egg wash by lightly mixing egg with a fork or whisk. Brush onto edges of pastry. 
‚Ä¢ Sprinkle desired amount of brown sugar and cinnamon over pastries and bake in oven @ 400 for 15-17 mins.
‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä‚†Ä

description:
Wholesome GO- TO weekday salad üíö 

Simple ingredients with a basic olive oil, vinegar dressing, but you i absolutely LOVE this as it is SO tasty & super easy to mix up! 
Save this recipe for a quick mid-week lunch üòç
If you are vegan , simply leave the feta out or replace it with alternatives. 

Ingredients: ( makes 2)
Quinoa: 1 cup
Cherry tomatoes: 300 grams cut in halves 
Small red onion: 1 sliced 
Large Avocado: 1  cut into chunks 
Parsley: 30 grams chopped 
Rocket leaves : 40 grams 
Feta: 40 grams ( SKIP IF VEGAN)
Dressing ingredients: 
Extra virgin olive oil: 3 tbsp 
Rice wine vinegar: 1 tbsp 
Chipotle chilli flakes : 1/2 tsp 
Tinned chickpeas: 1 ( optional for extra protein) 
Salt & pepper 

Steps:
1) cook quinoa. I cook mine in an electric rice cooker using 1:2 ratio of quinoa:water.
2) mix all the above salad ingredients. Add chickpeas if you are looking for extra protein. 
3) make the salad dressing by mixing together all the above ingredients listed for the dressings. The chipotle chilli flakes give it that extra edge üî• 
4) pour the dressing over the salad and give it a good mix. 
ENJOY!üòç

description:
Don't they look fabulous?? üòç
My favourite are the dark ones especially because the taste reminds me of ChristmasüéÑ - my favourite time of the year ü§≠‚ù§Ô∏èüíö

HEALTHY BLISS BALLS ü•úü••

‚Ä¢ BALLS WITH COCONUT FLOUR
Ingredients: 
- 5 dates
- 50g cashew nuts
- coconut flour 

1. Put dates in hot water for 10minutes to make them soft.
2. Blend cashew nuts then add dates and blend again until you get a smooth texture.
3. Form balls and roll them in coconut flour.
4. Put them in the refrigerator to rest for at least 1 hour.

üìùNutrition information
100g = 487 kcal
Fat: 29,7g
Carbohydrate: 41,2g
Protein: 13,5g 

‚Ä¢ BROWN BALLS
Ingredients:
- 50g raisin
- 40g walnut
- cinnamon

1. Put raisins in hot water for 10minutes to make them soft.
2. Blend walnuts, add raisins and cinnamon and blend again until you get a smooth and sticky texture.
3. Form balls and put them in the refrigerator to rest for 1 hour.

üìùNutrition information
100g = 484 kcal
Fat: 29g
Carbohydrate: 50,4g
Protein: 8,3g 

‚Ä¢ LIGHT BALLS
Ingredients:
- 50g almond
- 25g protein peanut butter with coconut
- 3 tsp coconut oil

1. Blend almonds then add peanut butter and coconut oil.
2. Blend until you get smooth and sticky texture.
3. Form balls and put them in the refrigerator to rest for 1 hour.

üìùNutrition information
100g = 625 kcal
Fat: 58,4g
Carbohydrate: 7,3g
Protein: 18,2g 

Enjoy!

description:
Ahhhh! Love to be close to the kitchen while I work‚Ä¶ Making these today for the family! Thanks Diane Dierking üíï

Strawberry Meringue Cookies
#yayforyummyandhealthyfood üòã

Ingredients:
7 egg whites
1/4 cup Splenda
1tsp. vanilla
1 package sugar-free strawberry jello
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line cookie sheet with parchment paper
Beat Egg Whites until fluffy. Gradually add Splenda, jello, and vanilla. Continue beating until soft peaks form.
Drop a teaspoon onto a covered cookie sheet
Bake for 10 min( do not let them brown)
Turn off heat and leave cookies in the closed oven until cookies are dry, generally at least 4 hours or overnight.

Makes 8 servings-
Per serving: ¬º ounce protein 1 ¬Ω condiment ¬Ω optional snack

description:
Enchilada Casserole: your new favorite 40 minute weeknight meal that fits your macros üëè

Ingredients:
1 lb turkey, ground
1 packet taco seasoning
20 oz enchilada sauce
1 onion
1 can corn
1 can black beans
1 can Rotel
6 Pea Protein tortillas
1 C mexican shredded cheese

Instructions:
1. Brown ground turkey in a pan and add taco seasoning (pro tip: do this over the weekend and stick in the fridge so this takes less time to put together!)
2. Preheat oven to 375F
3. Spread 1/2 of the can of enchilada sauce on the bottom of an 8x11 pan. Next, layer two tortillas, and half of each of the onion, corn, beans, and Rotel. Add some cheese. Repeat. For the top layer, add two tortillas, the rest of the enchilada sauce, and the rest of the cheese.
4. Bake for 30-35 minutes or until sauce is bubbling

Serves 5 for 438 kcals and 35g protein each!

Smokey pork with carrot & parsnip mash
430 calories 

This was last nights dinner, a quick and easy yet tasty and healthy bowl of goodness, and a great dish packed with veggies . 

Ingredients:
Serves 2
‚ñ´Ô∏è2 pork loins, fat removed and diced
‚ñ´Ô∏è1 onion cut into chunks
‚ñ´Ô∏è1 yellow pepper cut into chunks
‚ñ´Ô∏è200ml tomato passata

smokey pork with carrot & parsnip mash
430 calories 

this was last nights dinner, a quick and easy yet tasty and healthy bowl of goodness, and a great dish packed with veggies . 

ingredients:
serves 2 
2 pork loins, fat removed and diced
1 onion cut into chunks
1 yellow pepper cut into chunks
200 ml tomato passata 
2 teaspoon paprika 
dash worcestershire sauce
300 gram carrots diced
300 gram parsnips diced
bit of fresh parsley chopped

method 
boil a pan of water and add your carrots & parsnips (boil for roughly 20 minutes)
fry off your diced pork, pepper and onion in a hot pan for 5 minutes.
turn the heat down, pop on a lid and leave for a further 10 minutes.
add the passata, paprika & worcestershire sauce and simmer for 5 minutes or so.
mash your carrots and parsnips with a little reserved water , spoon into a bowl and top with the smokey pork.
garnish with the chopped parsley and serve with your favourite veg ( mine was served with steam pouch )

description:
Huevos rancheros

Ingredients:

- 1 red onion
-1 clove of garlic
-2 tomatoes (medium size)
-1-2 hot peppers (depending on how hot they are)
-6 tablespoons of beans (canned)
-1/3 teaspoon ground colorful pepper
-1/3 teaspoon cumin
-1/2 teaspoon of sweet smoked paprika
-2 tortillas
-4 eggs
-a little crumbled feta cheese (optional)
-salt (amount as desired)
-lard (for baking)

Preparation:

1. Melt the lard on a heated pan and briefly fry the sliced ‚Äã‚Äãonions and chopped hot peppers on it. Then add crushed garlic, sweet pepper and cumin and fry for a few more minutes.

2. Add the chopped tomatoes, saute them for a few minutes, add salt and pepper and towards the end add the canned beans. Remove the pan from the heat and set it aside.

3. In another clean pan, briefly fry the tortillas on one and the other side until they become crispy. When they are ready, take them out on plates and spread the sauteed vegetables on them. In the meantime, fry the eggs, arrange them on the tortillas and sprinkle with some crumbled cheese. Season with salt and pepper if necessary and add some more beans if you like.

Huevos rancheros is ready.Good apetit.

description:
Savor the end of Summer watermelon season with this delicious Watermelon salad! üçâ This salad is easy to make and deliciously refreshing! ‚òÄÔ∏è‚ú®

Save this post! Full recipe below! üëá
(For Printable Recipe Card and Notes: https://www.chewoutloud.com/watermelon-salad-recipe/) 

Ingredients: 

5 cups watermelon, cubed
1 1/2 cups yellow grape or cherry tomatoes, halved
1 small red onion, chopped
1/2 cup freshly torn basil leaves
1/4 cup freshly squeezed lime juice
2 TB pure honey
freshly ground black pepper to taste

Instructions: 

Combine: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Use rubber spatula to gently fold together until well combined.
Cover and Chill: Cover and chill no more than 1 hour before serving (watermelon salad is best served immediately.)

1 1 /2 cup yellow grape or cherry tomatoes, halved
1 small red onion, chopped
1/2 cup freshly torn basil leaves
1/4 cup freshly squeezed lime juice
2 tb pure honey
freshly ground black pepper to taste

instructions: 

combine: in a large bowl, combine all ingredients. use rubber spatula to gently fold together until well combined.
cover and chill: cover and chill no more than 1 hour before serving (watermelon salad is best served immediately.)
