description:
INGREDIENTS:
- 1 cup couscous
- 1 1/4 teaspoon salt
- 1 tablespoon olive oil
- 1 lemon
- 2 garlic cloves
- 3 tablespoon butter
- 1 pound raw shrimp, peeled
- 2 tablespoon chopped parsley 

INSTRUCTIONS

In a medium pot, bring 1 1/4 cups of water to a boil. Add coucous and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. Bring to a boil, then remove from the heat, cover and let stand for 5 minutes. When done, stir in olive oil, the juice from 1 lemon, and another 1/4 teaspoon of salt. Taste, and add additional olive oil and lemon to taste.

Mince the garlic. Pat the shrimp dry with a paper towel. In a large skillet over medium heat, melt the butter, then add garlic and cook for 30 seconds. Increase the heat to medium high and add the shrimp, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, and fresh ground pepper. Cool until the shrimp are opaque, about 3 minutes, turning once.

Serve the shrimp over couscous garnished with chopped parsley.

description:
GREEK LEMON CHICKEN SALAD

Ingredients:
1 cup (3.66 oz) Raw Cucumber, with peel
1 cup (5.26 oz) Raw Peppers, Red 
1 cup (6.34 oz) Raw Tomatoes 
8 olives Olives, Black 
18.2 oz Chicken, breast, boneless, skinless (raw) ~Should Yield 12 oz cooked
1 tsp Oil, olive 
2 tbsp dried Parsley 
1 clove Garlic, clove 
4 tsp Lemon or Lime Juice 
2 Tbsp Raw Onion 

Directions:
1. Preheat grill to medium-high heat.
2. Place chicken on grill when heated and cook about 5 minutes on each side, or until chicken is thoroughly cooked and no longer pink. Cut chicken into slices.
3. In a serving bowl, combine parsley, olives, and garlic. Whisk in 4 tsp lemon juice and 1 tsp olive oil. Add cucumber, bell pepper, tomato, and onion. Toss to coat ingredients with dressing. Add up to 1 tsp more of lemon juice to taste.
4. Split salad into two servings and place 6 oz chicken on top each salad.

Makes 2 servings

-

Ingredients:
- 1 tablespoon salted butter
- 2 ¬Ω cups milk chocolate
- 16 ounces mini marshmallows

Directions:

3. Bake for about 10 minutes, or until marshmallows are golden brown. Serve with graham crackers & enjoy!

description:
Are you feeling lazy? We have just the recipe for those days that you just don't feel like doing anything...This pasta dish only takes 20 minutes to cook and it tastes amazing!

FULL RECIPE HERE
‚Äã
‚ÄãIngredients:
‚Äã
Serves 2 
200g Dried pasta
1 tbsp Salt
70g Crusty bread
2 tbsp Olive oil
30g Butter
70g Hazelnuts
1 Garlic clove cracked open
150g Asparagus
150g Taleggio cheese
1 handful of Parsley chopped
‚Äã
Here‚Äôs how:
‚Äã
Cook the pasta in a large pan of salted, boiling water for 9-10 minutes.
Meanwhile snap the asparagus in half and where it naturally breaks that‚Äôs where it's tender and put to one side.
Chop the bread up into small pieces and place on a non-stick baking tray.
Pour over a drizzle of oil and bake in a pre-heated oven at 170c for 10 minutes or just until crisp.
Meanwhile melt the butter in a large pan with the cracked garlic clove.
Chop the hazelnuts into chunks and add to the pan with the butter and garlic.
Lift out a ladle of pasta water and add to the butter with a little  black pepper.
This will make an emulsion-style sauce.
Lay the asparagus into the sauce and pop the lid onto the pan to speed up the cooking process without evaporating the sauce too much.
When the pasta has cooked for 9 minutes, lift out of the water and add to the pan.
Stir together and top with chopped parsley and diced cheese.
Finish with a drizzle of extra virgin olive oil and scatter over the breadcrumbs.¬†
‚Äã
#nationallazyday #lazyday #lazy #recipe #easymeals #tenminmeal #qucikmeals #masterclass #pastadish #pasta #dinner #recipeidea #recipeideas

description:
The best summer days are spent eating s‚Äômores üç´

@TheDIYMoms have teamed up with some creative mamas to celebrate National S‚Äômores Day!

Love to make these no bake s‚Äômores bars!

Ingredients: 
Cooking spray
3 Tablespoons salted butter, melted
1 10 ounce bag mini marshmallows, divided
5 cups Golden Grahams cereal
1 cup chocolate chips + 1 small handful

Spray a 13 x 9 pan with cooking spray and line it with parchment paper

Melt butter over medium heat in pot. Once it's melted, reduce the heat to low.‚Ä®
Set aside 1 cup of mini marshmallows + 1 small handful from the 10 oz bag and add the remaining marshmallows to pot. Spray a mixing spoon with cooking spray and continuously stir until marshmallows are fully melted.‚Ä®
Remove the pot from the heat and add the Golden Grahams. Stir well to combine. Then add the reserved cup of mini marshmallows and the cup of chocolate chips (leaving the handfuls aside).‚Ä®
Stir once more to combine and then put the mixture into the prepared 13 x 9 pan. Gently press it down into an even layer in the pan.‚Ä®
Top with handfuls of extra marshmallows and chocolate chips to your taste and let it set in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes ‚Ä®
Enjoy!!

Check out #DIYMomsSmores to see s‚Äômore great ideas!

#TheDIYMoms #DIYMomsSummer 
#nationalsmoresday #smoresbar #smoresseason #smorestime #recipeshare #recipeideas #recipesharing #recipebook

description:
Classic Cottage Pie ü•ß üëåüèº

Ingredients:

For the mash: 
- 1.5 kg Maris Piper potatoes, peeled and cut into cubes
- whole milk x 125ml
- double cream x 4 Tbsp
- unsalted butter x 4 Tbsp
- salt and pepper to taste 

For the filling:

- mince beef x 500g
- frozen mixed vege x 2 C
- Worcester sauce x 1 Tbsp
- salt and pepper to taste 
- tomato ketchup x 2 Tbsp 
- tomato pur√©e x 4 tsp
- 400ml chicken stock 
- parsley x 4 Tbsp
- 1 Tbsp Italian herbs
- 1 tsp salt and 1 tsp pepper
- garlic paste x 1 tsp 
- onion x 2, finely chopped 
- corn flour x 2 Tbsp

Steps:

üëâ Preheat oven to 180 degrees Celcius 

üëâ Cover the potatoes with cold water and bring to boil. Add 1 tsp salt. Leave to summer till potatoes are soft.

üëâ Drain the potatoes and transfer to a large bowl. Add the spices, butter, milk and cream and start mashing with a masher till it is soft 

üëâ Meanwhile prepare the filling. Heat 2 Tbsp olive oil then add onions and garlic and fry for a minute.

üëâ Add the minced beef, saut√© till browned. Add the parsley, frozen vege, tomato pur√©e, ketchup, Worcester sauce, corn flour, and chicken stock. Keep stirring and mixing over low heat for 5 minutes. Add spices 

üëâ Spoon the meat into the base of an oven-proof dish. Too with the mashed potatoes. Make a design with a fork

üëâ Place the fish into the oven for 15 minutes 

Bon Appetite üòä

 add the minced beef, saut√© till browned. add the parsley, frozen vege, tomato pur√©e, ketchup, worcester sauce, corn flour, and chicken stock. keep stirring and mixing over low heat for 5 minutes. add spices 

 spoon the meat into the base of an oven-proof dish. too with the mashed potatoes. make a design with a fork

 place the fish into the oven for 15 minutes 

bon appetite

description:
We know what you‚Äôre thinking, but don‚Äôt knock it till you try it!

Durian is notorious for its strong smell, but don‚Äôt let the aroma turn you away from attempting this Durian cake by Aunty D. It‚Äôs sweet, toothsome and imbued with buttery durian flavour, but not overpoweringly so ‚Äì a bizarre treat to blow anyone‚Äôs mind!

Here‚Äôs how you make it!

Ingredients:

Margarine 125 g
Sugar 125 g
Eggs 2
Durian 1 ¬Ω cup
Vanilla 2 tsp
Flour 125 g
Baking Soda ¬Ω tsp

Method:

To a large bowl, add butter and sugar and whisk to combine. 

Continue whisking, adding one egg at a time until the mixture reaches a smooth texture.

Mix the deseeded durian flesh and vanilla into the bowl.

In a separate bowl, combine flour and baking soda and incorporate the dry ingredients with the wet ingredients.

Fold the batter thoroughly to remove any lumps, pour into a lined baking tin and bake at 150 ¬∞C for 35 to 40 minutes.

Once it‚Äôs out of the oven, let the cake cool down, grab a slice and enjoy!

-
-

description:
Pina Colada Bounty Bars are exist and these are the healthy version of the bars! So refreshing bars that can brisk your summer vibes üççüç´

Ingredients:
-50 gr frozen pineapple @furouindonesia
-50 gr coconut flakes @nourish_indonesia
-1 tbsp maple syrup
-1 tsp lime juice
-a pinch of salt @puraindonesia @purakitchen 

Coating:
-80 gr dark chocolate (I use dark chocolate cooking couverture 73% @cauchocolatesbali)
-1 tsp coconut oil @nutiva

Toppings (optional):
dessicated coconut

Portions:
4-5 bars (each bar approximately 25-30 gr)

Instructions:
1. Put all ingredients into food processor.
2. Place the mixture into bars silicon moulding and in the freezer for 15 minutes.
3. With double boiler, melt the dark chocolate. Add 1 tsp coconut oil when in the middle of melting process. 
4. Take out the bars from bars silicon moulding, place them in baking parchment paper and coat with melted dark chocolate. 
5. Optionally you can put dessicated coconut on top of each bar.
6. Place in the fridge for 15 minutes. Enjoy afterwards!

description:
#healthyheart A bright salad with creamy hearts of palm, orange supremes and english cucumber with citrus honey dijon dressing. [Author: Lisa Lotts | Garlic & Zest]

INGREDIENTS:
for the dressing:
üî≤1 teaspoon orange zest
üî≤1 clove garlic minced
üî≤1 tablespoon whole grain dijon mustard
üî≤1 1/2 tablespoons cider vinegar
üî≤2 tablespoons honey preferably a citrus honey
üî≤3 tablespoons olive oil
üî≤1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
üî≤1/4 teaspoon black pepper

for the salad
üî≤1 14-oz can whole hearts of palm drained, sliced crosswise into 1/4" rounds
üî≤2 large oranges supremed
üî≤1/2 english cucumber thinly sliced into half moons
üî≤2 radishes cut into matchsticks
üî≤1/4 medium red onion very thinly sliced
üî≤1/4 cup microgreens (optional)

INSTRUCTIONS:
make the dressing:
üî≥In a small bowl, combine all the ingredients for the dressing and whisk to combine.  Set aside.

make the salad:
üî≥In a wide, shallow bowl combine the hearts of palm, orange supremes, cucumber, radishes and red onion.  Add about 3 tablespoons of dressing and toss to combine.  If the salad needs more dressing, add it one tablespoon at a time, but don't overdress.  Sprinkle micro greens over the salad and serve.

description:
üòã Today‚Äôs recipe is perfect to go down a treat. Topped with fresh juicy üçë plums and swaddled in a sweet, creamy custard topping - a slice of our lovely üç∞ Spiced Plum Custard Cake will leave you wanting more in anytime of the day. The hint of Alce Nero Organic Plum Jam is simply a cherry on the cake! üòç

üç∞ üíï A Slice Of Happiness: Spiced Plum Custard Cake

Ingredients: 
- 1 ¬Ω cups Alce Nero Organic Plum Jam
- 1 cup all-purpose flour
- 1 tbsp  white sugar
- 1 tbsp baking powder
- 1/2 cup butter- cold, cut into cubes
- 2 tbsp heavy cream
- 1 egg
- 1 cup plums, pitted and sliced 
- 1/2 tsp cinnamon
- 1/4 tsp ground ginger
- 1/4 tsp ground nutmeg

To Make Custard Topping: 
- 1/2 cup heavy cream
- 1/2 cup white sugar
- 1 egg
- 1 tsp vanilla extract

Preparation: 
1) Preheat oven to 350 ¬∞C. Lightly spray an 8 inch springform pan  and set aside.
Toss the plums with the spices and set aside. In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar and baking powder. Add cubes of butter. Stir in vanilla, Alce Nero Organic Plum Jam, heavy cream and egg. Continue to stir for a few seconds of until well combined. 
2) Turn the dough into the bottom of the pan and press in with your fingers. Arrange the spiced plums over the dough. Bake for 20-25 minutes.
3) While cake is baking prep the custard by whisking together the cream, sugar, vanilla and egg.
4) When the cake is done baking, pour the custard over the plums, and return to the oven, bake for another 20-25 minutes or until the custard has set. Serve warm and enjoy! 

üòç Enjoy making easy and delicious dessert recipes with Alce Nero Organic Jams. Shop now at: https://linktr.ee/alcenero. Link in bio.

description:
„ÄêMiso Moist and Juicy Chicken Ham„Äë
This is the dish which you can easily make with microwave. Thanks to miso, the chicken is moist and juicy. You can serve the chicken juice as soup rich in umami from both miso and chicken.

‚è±Estimated Cooking Time: 10 minutes or less

üç≥Ingredients: For 2 servings
1 Chicken breast (300 g/ 11 oz)
1 Japanese green onion (Chives or Corianders)
2 tbsp Organic Miso White
Pinch of Black pepper
2 tbsp Cooking sake
200 ml (6.8 fl oz) Water
1 piece Ginger
[A]
1 tbsp Sesame oil
1/4 tsp Salt
Pinch of Black pepper

üç≥Instructions
1. Poke chicken breast a few times with a fork. Massage it with miso and black pepper in a big heat-resistant bowl and set aside for 10 minutes.

2. Place the chicken breast (from instruction 1) with the skin-side up and roll it to make a chicken stick. Peel and thinly slice a 1 inch (2.5 cm) piece of ginger. Add cooking sake, water and gingers. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap loosely and microwave it at 1200W for 2 minutes 45 seconds. Let it cool. (Cooking time depends on the wattage of your microwave.)

3. Cut the white part of Japanese green onion into strips. Chives or corianders can be used instead of Japanese green onion. Combine [A] for sauce.

4. Cut the breast (from instruction 2) into diagonal pieces approx. 0.4 inch (1 cm) thick.

5. Transfer the chicken on a plate with the sauce (from instruction 3) on top. Serve the liquid left in the bowl in a small bowl as chicken soup.

#Japanesefood #koji #recipe #fermentedfood #cookingram #itadakimasu #homecooking #buzzfeedfood #eattheworld #healthyrecipes #hikarimiso

description:
Whip it up Wednesday!! 

I made My yummy dish that we like to call in our home chicken chunk!

Do you like to eat it in a variety of ways either with crackers or in a rap not only do we devour it quickly but so did my boys! 

Here‚Äôs the recipe below try it out and let me know what you think!! 

Ingredients:

2 cups of chopped up rotisserie chicken ( are use the pre-packed pulled apart chicken from Costco) 

1 chopped Serano pepper
3 Chopped stocks of celery
2  diced tomatoes
1 small red onion chopped

2 Tbs of Mayonnaise made with avocado oil ( I use primal kitchen mayo brand) 

To taste add sea salt and pepper

Mix all ingredients together in bowl for best flavors place in Tupperware and set in fridge for overnight or you can eat soon after finished!! 

Enjoy!!! #dontovercomplicate #healthyrecipes #momofboys #stayontrack

description:
Baba Ghanoug. This dip is made of roasted eggplants, tomatoes and onions combined with raw garlic, parsley and mint, tossed with pomegranate molasses, lemon juice and olive oil.
Follow‚û°Ô∏è @homerecipes101 
Facebook‚û°Ô∏è homerecipes101 
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
INGREDIENTS:
2 Eggplants
2 Tomatoes 
1 Large onion
2 cloves of garlic, crushed
1/4 Cup fresh mint, chopped 
1/4 Cup fresh parsley, chopped 
2 1/2 Tbsp fresh lemon juice
1 1/2 Tbsp pomegranate molasses 
1/4 Cup extra virgin olive oil
Sea salt and pepper

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Preheat oven or grill to 500¬∞F. Pierce each eggplant with a knife on both sides. Place the eggplants on the grill or baking sheet if using the oven, along with the tomatoes and onion. Grill or bake until the eggplant is completely soft on the inside. (Veggies are grilled in this recipe).
2. Once the veggies are ready, peel off the skin and let it cool completely.
3. Chop the eggplants, onion and tomatoes, add them in large bowl.
4. Mash the grilled veggies with a fork or a potato masher into a chunky texture.
5. Add parsley, mint, garlic, lemon juice, pomegranate molasses, olive oil, salt and pepper. Combine well.
6. Pour the Baba Ghanoug in a smaller bowl, drizzle with a little bit of extra olive oil. Usually served with bread.

description:
Where are my SNICKERS lovers at? üç´

Check out these HEALTHY HOMEMADE SNICKERS BARS!! They are filled with protein and will definitely fix that sweet tooth ü§©

Ingredients:
1.5 cups Greek yogurt
1.5 scoops of Level 1 Protein Powder (either Milk Chocolate, Ice Cream Sandwich or Caramel Latte)
1/2 cup 1st Phorm Nut Butter
2 tbsp unsweetened almond milk
2 tbsp sugar free maple syrup
1/2 cup dark chocolate chips
1 tsp coconut oil

Directions:
- Mix together Greek yogurt protein powder until creamy. Spread mixture into a parchment
lined 8√ó4 loaf pan. Place in freezer for 2 hours to harden.

- Mix together nut butter, almond milk and maple syrup. Pour caramel layer over hardened Greek yogurt layer and place in freezer again for approx. 1 hour or until hardened. 

- Melt chocolate and coconut oil in 30 second increments until smooth. Remove batter from freezer. Slice into 8 bars and drizzle with dark chocolate. Place back in freezer until hardened.

- Keep stored in freezer and enjoy!

Macros P: 14 C: 17 F: 12

description:
HAPPY WEDNESDAY üíöüíö

I hope everyone is having a great week üòåüòåüòå if you are looking for a mid week pick me up you need to make this dinner!! Had this tonight, and it was amazing! Never disappoints and so so so easy to make!! 

Dinner #dEATS : oven baked salmon with a lemon dijon glaze with brown rice and steamed broccoli on the side!!

Salmon recipe (serves 2):

Ingredients:
- 2 salmon filets
- 2 tbsp dijon mustard
- 2 tbsp maple syrup (or sub honey)
- 1 tbsp chopped fresh rosemary
- zest of a lemon 
- 1/2 tsp of salt and pepper 

Directions:
1. preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
2. season salmon filets with salt and pepper.
3. stir together the rosemary, mustard, maple syrup or honey, and lemon zest. Spread the mixture on the salmon and let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes.
4. top the salmon with thin slices of lemon and bake for about 15 to 20 minutes (depending on the size of the filets).
5. let the salmon rest for five minutes and serve! 

Don‚Äôt forget to smile üòÅ
- @abbeynechanicky

description:
Eggplant dish ,a great appetizer as well 
Ingredients:
-eggplants: 2-3, peeled, add some salt, let it sit for at least 1 hour, rinse them, and then saut√© them in some oil.
-onions: 2-3 medium size, chopped finely and saut√© them for 20 minutes on low heat until golden brown. 
-dried mint: 1/2 teaspoon to add to the eggplants and 1/2 tablespoon to be heated lightly with some oil for garnish 
-whey ( KASHK) :  a few tablespoons , you can substitute whey with a thick yogurt or you may buy them from a Persian store. I usually boil whey with some water for 20 minutes on low heat before using it.
Cooking direction :
After saut√©ing the eggplants put them in a pot, add one cup water, a few dashes of turmeric, and 1/2 teaspoon dried mint, and cook it for 25 minutes. Remove some of the oil from the pot and smash the eggplants well with a wooden spoon. For the garnish we use lightly heated dried mint with some oil, saut√©ed onions, and some Whey ( or thick yogurt). Enjoy

description:
Celly¬Æ Granola Recipeü•£ 

Ingredients:
- 2 cups old fashioned rolled oats
- 1 cup unsalted nuts (walnuts, almonds, pecans or hazelnuts)
- 1/2 cup Celly Salt¬Æ Roasted Pepitas
- 1/2 cup vanilla pea protein powder
- 1/4 cup hulled unsalted sunflower seeds
- 1/4 cup flaxseed meal
- 2 tsp ground cinnamon
- 1/2 tsp Celly Salt¬Æ Original
- 1/3 cup maple syrup
- 1/3 cup coconut oil

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 325¬∞. 
2. Combine oats with Celly Salt¬Æ Original in a large bowl; stir to combine.
3. Pour maple syrup and coconut oil over dry ingredients. Stir well to coat evenly.
4. Pour granola into a rimmed baking sheet and spread in an even layer.
5. Bake for 30 minutes, stirring halfway through, or until golden. Cool completely in pan. Store in an airtight container.

Enjoy. ü§ç

(Note: Recipes are also on www.cellysalt.com)

description:
Cheesy Cauliflower Tater Tots

Ingredients:
4 cups (14.08 oz) cauliflower florets (8 greens)
2 tbsp heavy cream (2 condiments)
2 tbsp butter (4 healthy fat)
1/2 cup (2 oz) shredded low fat sharp cheddar cheese (1/2 lean)
7 egg whites (1/2 leanest)
¬Ω tsp pepper (1 condiment)
¬º tsp salt (1 condiment)
10 sprays non-stick spray (1 condiment)

Directions:
Clean and trip the cauliflower, adding the florets to a microwave safe bowl. Add the cream and butter to the bowl. Microwave for 5 minutes. Add the cauliflower and cheese to a magic bullet or food processor and blend until still chunky ‚Äì kind of like a cooked oatmeal consistency. Season with salt and pepper. Chill for the last half hour. Whip the egg whites to a stiff peak. Fold 1/3 of the egg whites into the cauliflower mixture to lighten it up. Then fold the cauliflower mixture into the rest of the egg whites and gently mix until combined. For best results, chill for another half hour or they won‚Äôt hold their shape well. Fit a pastry bag with a round or star tube with about ¬æ inch opening. Spray the inside of the bag with nonstick spray. Gently squeeze out 1 inch sections onto a greased cookie sheet, cutting with a butter knife as you go. When finished, bake in a 375 degree oven for 10-12 minutes or longer until puffed and slightly browned. Remove from the oven and serve.

Makes 4 servings
Per serving: 1/4 protein, 2 vegetables, 1 ¬º condiments, 1 healthy fat
‚ù§Ô∏èüòé Coach Kat

description:
Raise your hand if you love peachesüôã‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èüôã‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

If you raised your hand then you will love this peach dessert!üçë

Filling Ingredients:
6 -8peaches
2 tablespoons of chia seeds
1 piece of fresh ginger grated 
4 tablespoons of honey 
1 lemon

Topping ingredients:
1/2 cup of gluten free flour 
1/2 cup of almond flour
1/4 cup of honey 
1/4 cup of melted butter 
1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon 

Directions:
Pre heat oven to 400 degrees
Cut up peaches (I like to leave the skin on)
In a large bowl toss peaches, chia seeds, Ginger, honey, juice of 1 lemon
Add peach mixture to pie plate set side while you make the crumble 
In a medium size bowl add 
1/2 cup almond flour 
1/2 cup gluten free flour 
1/4 cup grass fed butter softened 
1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.. I like to do this part with my hand mix it up and crumble on top of peaches 
Put in oven and lower to 375 bake for 30-35 minutes or until the juices are bubbly and the crumble is golden.. 
Serve with Vanilla ice cream and enjoy! üçëüç¶

description:
CREAMY GARLIC TUSCAN SHRIMP üç§ 

Serves 4
Per serving: ¬Ω leanest, 2 fats, ~3 condiments, 1 green

Ingredients:
2 cloves garlic, finely diced
1 pound (500 g) shrimp (or prawns) -- tails on or off
¬Ω cup diced green onions
.25 oz sundried tomatoes (just dried; not packed in oil)
1 ¬Ω cups half and half (can use 1 ¬Ω cups unsweetened almond or cashew milk; this would result in 0 healthy fats per serving ; to keep condiments to 3, reduce parmesan cheese to 2 Tbsp if using the milk)
¬º tsp each- salt and pepper
4 cups baby spinach leaves
1/4 cup fresh grated Parmesan cheese (do not include for dairy free option)
¬Ω teaspoons dried Italian herbs
1 tablespoon fresh parsley, chopped

Directions:

1. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add in the garlic and fry until fragrant (about one minute). Add in the shrimp and fry two minutes on each side, until cooked through and pink. Transfer to a bowl; set aside.
2. Fry the green onions in the skillet. Add the sun dried tomatoes and fry for 1-2 minutes to release their flavors.
3. Reduce heat to low-medium heat, add the half and half and bring to a gentle simmer, while stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper to your taste.
4. Add in the spinach leaves and allow to wilt in the sauce, and add in the parmesan cheese. Allow sauce to simmer for a further minute until cheese melts through the sauce. (For a thicker sauce, add the half and half mixture to the center of the pan, and continue to simmer while quickly stirring the mixture through until the sauce thickens.)
5. Add the shrimp back into the pan; sprinkle with the herbs and parsley, and stir through.
6. Serve over 2 steamed steamed veg. 
or 1 cup cauliflower rice.
‚Äîfor a full lean amd green add 1 1/2 lbs more shrimp. #healthyrecipes #hudsonhealthcoach
